text: 2018 has marked a colossal change for women and #female #empowerment, but there is still so much to achieve. this year we have finally come out thanks to the #metoo movement which is only now shaping the film industry like never before. finally silencing & convicting those men who took advantage of young women for too many years. many of us experienced such harassments and we all know that those scares will carry through our life without shame. after gathering strength and courage this year, i conquered one of my greatest fears: visually voicing those concerns, issues that people don’t like discussing but shouldn’t be overlooked. diving into the world of female creative art direction, i was incredibly lucky to have the opportunity of shaping @govoltmobility’s brand identity, my partner’s startup, @giulianoblei , a visionary who’s never doubted my true potential. i thank him above all for his support, constant love and determination, i have learnt so much this past year. to my beloved friends @caro__roca @tashalash @valentina1romano who’ve helped me through this year’s emotional turmoils. so much excitement and change awaits me as i embark this glorious 2019. my intention is to live this year fearlessly, to break those archaic social barriers that for too long have clouded my country 🇮🇹 #newyear #womanempowerment #women #donna #womeninfilm #goals #gains #director #creativeartdirector #donnenelcinema #motovation #love #selflove #inspiration #lifestyle  #mindset

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
be loved – это принципиально новый подход к уходу за кожей для тех, кто:
• ищет персональную программу ухода, • хочет, чтобы косметика "работала", • обращает особне внимание на качество и безопасность косметики. ✨в основе косметики be loved – 3 эксклюзивных комплекса для увлажнения, ремоделирования и клеточного восстановления, десятки ценных масел и растительных экстрактов. 🎯с косметикой be loved ты сможешь:
✔️ создать индивидуальную программу ухода за кожей,
✔️ обеспечить уход, подходящий под особенности твоей кожи, сохраняя ее молодость и красоту. 💜выбери нежные базовые средства для деликатного ежедневного ухода и дополни их масками и сыворотками направленного действия для решения индивидуальных проблем кожи.

text:
powerful words i frequently like to remind myself of, shared by the beautiful meghan markle. happy new year everyone 💕⠀
⠀
'i no longer have patience for certain things, not because i’ve become arrogant, but simply because i reached a point in my life where i do not want to waste more time with what displeases me or hurts me.⠀
-⠀
i have no patience for cynicism, excessive criticism and demands of any nature. i lost the will to please those who do not like me, to love those who do not love me and to smile at those who do not want to smile at me.⠀
-⠀
i no longer spend a single minute on those who lie or want to manipulate. i decided not to coexist anymore with pretence, hypocrisy, dishonesty and cheap praise.⠀
i do not tolerate selective erudition nor academic arrogance. i do not adjust either to popular gossiping.⠀
-⠀
i hate conflict and comparisons. i believe in a world of opposites and that’s why i avoid people with rigid and inflexible personalities. in friendship i dislike the lack of loyalty and betrayal.⠀
-⠀
i do not get along with those who do not know how to give a compliment or a word of encouragement. exaggerations bore me and i have difficulty accepting those who do not like animals.⠀
-⠀
and on top of everything i have no patience for anyone who does not deserve my patience.'⠀
⠀
————————————————————⠀
⠀

text:
.
페미니스트들의 기념일을 담은
2019년 상반기(1~6월)
페미 캘린더(femi-calendar).
.
각 달에 관련된 이야기, 
작업의 뒷이야기를 소개합니다.
.
🖤1월의 부제🖤
girls can do anything in 2019.
.
🖤기념일🖤
1/1(호주제 폐지 기념일) 
1/6(잔다르크 탄생일)
1/9(시몬 드 보부아르 탄생일) 
1/11(권기옥 탄생)
1/20(여성행진 뉴욕) 
1/25(버지니아 울프 탄생일) 
1/30(검찰 내 성폭력 고발 #metoo)
.
🖤작업 코멘트🖤
1월에는 기념할 날이 많았다. 나는 가능한 이 기념일들을 모두 달력에 실어보고 싶었다. 그래서 8개의 기념일을 각각 작은 일러스트로 나타내 보았다.
특별히 신경썼던 점은 시몬 드 보부아르나 버지니아 울프를 그릴 때 진지한 느낌으로 그리려고 했다는 점이다. 올해 variety의 표지를 장식한 로빈 라이트의 사진을 인상 깊게 본 기억이 있는데, 그처럼 여성이 심각한 표정으로 그러지는 경우를 나는 많이 보지 못했다. 그래서 이번에 이 여성 인물들을 그릴 때는 진중하고 심각한 표정으로 그리고 싶었다.
.
페미 캘린더는 페미니스트에게 중요한 의미를 갖는 기념일을 기반으로, 여성 디자이너들이 2019년의 달력을 만드는 “페미톤” 워크샵(11/17)에서 나온 결과물입니다. 6인의 디자이너들은 각자 맡은 달의 기념일을 직접 조사하고, 토론을 거쳐 월별 기념일과 테마를 선정했습니다.
.
페미 캘린더는 프로필 하단 링크를 통해
누구나 다운 받아 사용할 수 있습니다✔️
.
.
.
#feminist #feminism #femicalendar #calendar #design #vvcd #페미톤

페미 캘린더는 페미니스트에게 중요한 의미를 갖는 기념일을 기반으로, 여성 디자이너들이 2019년의 달력을 만드는 “페미톤” 워크샵(11/17)에서 나온 결과물입니다. 6인의 디자이너들은 각자 맡은 달의 기념일을 직접 조사하고, 토론을 거쳐 월별 기념일과 테마를 선정했습니다.
.
페미 캘린더는 프로필 하단 링크를 통해
누구나 다운 받아 사용할 수 있습니다✔️
.
.
.

text:
let's close our eyes and connect to our own beauty.  how would that change our world? 
what makes you special?  what are you really good at? 
everyone has it.  is it your eyes that twinkle and smile? your sharp wit?  your crooked smile?  do you love to dance?  can you sense another's feelings?  do you have a knack for numbers? spoken word? 
i challenge you today. 
as we begin this new year, 
choose one thing (i am sure you have many that you could pick) to commit to nurturing in yourself this year.  if you write, commit to making time to write each day.  if you sing, take time each day to practice.  do math.  code.  reach out to a friend.  draw a picture. 
whatever it is.  do it.  it's an investment.  and you are worth it!  #womeninpolitics #womenleadership #womeningovernment #nastywomen #genderequality #metoo #timesup #womensmarch #womenvote #womenswave #whyimarch #imarchfor #equality #womensrights #feminism #feminist #intersectionalfeminism #intersectional #futureisfemale #femaleempowerment #girlsrule #girlsruntheworld #girlboss #ladyboss #ovarygang #girlpower #grlpower #womensupportingwomen #eeoc #diversity

text:
happy new year! 🥳 
i won’t bore you with the basics; i took a break from instagram to be with my 3 amazing kids and family. i am most grateful for my children. that they are healthy, smart, loving and kind to others and to this world. i need to be more mindful of how much i have and less on what i want in 2019. i need to be more mindful that many mothers/fathers do not have their children with them, or have children that are sick. at the end of the day, at the end of the year, the only true thing that really matters to me is my children’s health and happiness. i’ll be focused on that, which will mean i’m on here less. 
i think i have a bit of blogger/influencer fatigue and i care much less about follower numbers and engagement rates than i did this time last year. dramatically less.
i’d really like to focus on small, local, or women owned as best i can while making a living (a very hard thing to do these days in any field). this does not minimize how thankful and happy all my collaborations have made me in terms of friendship, insight, travel, fun and wellness.
i just don’t care, if i’m brutally honest, about the competition, the stats, who has fake followers, if i have fake followers, if she/he has more followers or less. i just care immensely less about those things at this point. #newyearnewmebullshit 
so i’ll focus on my children, my wellness, local, small business and empowering women. when amazing collaborations come along i will absolutely share with all of you. 
let’s all stand together instead of in comparison🥰
ps- i hope i keep this positive focus all year #newyearnewgoals #cheerstoanewyear

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
my #hope for #2019 is simple: make the new year better than the old one! when i post this pic, it is #2019 in the eastern and central time zones. for the new year, the keyword will be hope:
.
hope to find a place i can call my own.
hope for a better job.
hope to travel to more places i've never been to before.
hope to meet that special lady to spend the rest of my life with.
hope for a better life overall.
.
and i hope that there's a significant seismic change in our country - not only at 1600 pennsylvania avenue in our nation's capital, but in the attitudes of the american people - to end the divisions that have shaken the confidence of the vast majority of us americans. let's continue the #metoo movement. let's stomp out bullying. let's finally stop racism dead in its tracks. and let's force the powers that be that it's the 99% of us that have the power to change the world for the better!
.
as the late @johnlennonofficial said in his 1971 classic song "imagine", "you may say i'm a dreamer, but i'm not the only one." my hope for #2019 is the same thing most people are hoping for - to achieve bigger goals, to be better versions of ourselves and to make our nation better than the last couple of years. #happynewyear #newyearsday2019

text:
one of our big goals for 2019 is to share more diversity in our feed. we follow lots of fabulous men & women and we really want to celebrate and champion intersectional feminism.
we are painfully aware that we are 3 white women essentially selling “feminist tee feminism”
not a particular brand we want to be associated with. 
yes, we are selling tees, but we are selling tees with purpose! 
we don’t keep a single dollar- every last brass razoo we make is donated back into the community and put into the hands of not-for-profits who are making huge and very real differences in lives of women and families all across australia. .
“feminist tee feminism” is about buying a tee from a business that keep the profits, that usually has ripped off the slogan or catchphrase and offered nothing new. they are jumping on the bandwagon of “body posi” and cashing in on the #metoo movement.
we aren’t just selling tees (well, we are) but we we are working our asses off to provide support and show support to women in our country who are in pain.
our shirts have an original concept (thanks @kimbarnard), original design (thanks @northsouthgracewest). our shirts are printed by lady startup sisters in brisbane at @thetshirtmill and the tees we use have been ethically sourced- so we can guarantee they are not made in sweatshops & factories underpaying women and child workers... which defeats the whole fucking purpose of a feminist tee! @thetshirtmill have generously donated an extra 10% of the profits on all our products sold to our charities as well. (that’s amazing!) .
we are just trying to make as much money as possible and get it into the right hands. 
so this year, when you choose to support a business that says they ‘donate to charities’ ask questions, because if they are donating $1 from every $40 tee sold then maybe reconsider the tee and just donate the $40 to your favourite charity instead. 
this year we want to see more women of colour, women wearing hijabs, women with disabilties, lgbtq and also men & children too. we want to embrace our diverse country and include everyone in our feminism.
tag your mates who you think can help us, rep our tees & get our cause out there.

text:
i’d be lying if i said that 2018 was the absolute best year of my life so far. it was a great year, however the beginning of 2018 really tested me; my survival techniques were tested, my sanity, my strength, and my self-love was strained. i learned real quick that no one is there for you more than yourself. you are your own fountain of happiness. you control how you react to those around you and how they may treat you. you deserve the absolute world; whether you’re an ex of mine or someone i’ve never met, you deserve the best. i am extremely blessed with the way things have come together at the end of 2018. i am at peace, i am constantly working to let go of my past and continue to love myself through my struggles. my depression does not define me; i am stronger than i give myself credit for. to my mom, family, and friends, thank you for loving me regardless of my flaws, my ego, and my stubbornness. you’ve taught me unconditional love and support for someone who felt like they deserved nothing. i can honestly and truly say that without grasping a fearful opportunity by the hands and jumping, i wouldn’t have been able to make the growth i did these past six months.
•
•
•
if you struggle with depression, anxiety, ptsd, or any other mental health illness...take your time with healing. one day it will click and you’ll be ready. but he ready because you are ready, not because other people are telling you to be ready. getting help is 150% worth it. you aren’t weak for seeking help in any way! trust me.
•
•
•
if you ever need an unbiased ear to lean on, my inbox is always open. you are never alone. you are loved. you matter.
•
•
•
•

text:
you matter - demetrius harmon @demetriusharmon 
i chose to write my first article on the popular yet growing hoodie line you matter by demetrius harmon. 
vine sensational turned internet comedian has used his platform to not only bring awareness to mental health but also to showcase these bomb ass hoodies as well, i mean it is hoodie season right?... colors come in red/blue/grey/and tan. the words “you matter” are perfectly placed directly in the center of the hoodie. this powerful statement not only makes you feel empowered, it empowers anyone who reads it. on the left arm it says “i feel weak” while on the right it say “but i know i’m strong”. a true testament to a brave soldier fighting the battle of mental health. with this small but strong piece it has shown that you can be vulnerable yet powerful. which is the beauty behind the pain. i myself can not wait to get my hands on one and in due time i will! but until then everyone go on over to his website and check em out! unisex hoodies in all sizes. and always remember “you matter!” https://www.shopdemetriusharmon.com

#youmatter #mentalhealth #youarestrong #neveralone #speakup #metoo #newlife #newbeginnings #fashionblogger #blog #bloggerstyle #fashion #fashionista #mensfashion #womansfashion #brand

text:
f o u r // ways to find a healthy relationship #advocate #idaho——————————————————————
i’m this coming year, we hope  healthy relationships remain healthy, and that those who are seeking a healthy relationship may find it.
it’s not uncommon for a batterer to be the most charming person in the room when you first meet them. it’s not uncommon for them to be attractive, attentive, romantic, and thoughtful, and even kind. a batterer may keep their desire to exert power and control over a victim secret, typically revealing it only after they’ve charmed their way into someone’s life. 
it’s not you fault if you’ve fallen into this ruse. the most common age in which intimate partner violence first occurs is 18-24 years old for both women and men — aka the dating years. which is why it’s vitally important to be selective about who we date as they could wind up being our lifelong partner.
carol wick is ceo of harbor house of central florida, a domestic violence outreach and education program, as well as an emergency shelter. swipe through to read the four tips she has offered to help people attract and recognize healthy relationships. —————————————————————— #lifestyle #family #loveshouldnthurt #december #enddv #byui #dvfacts #dancing #entrepreneur #fall #design #wellness #marketing #friends #idaho #timesup #metoo #idaho #health #breakthesilence #idaho #graphicdesign #healthy #winter

*
it’s official! 365 days are in the books!
*
i was really excited when the journey started. some days that changed. some days i didn’t feel like it. some days i felt like it wasn’t making a difference. some days i felt like a slave to the process instead of a participant in the process.
*
i’m glad i didn’t give up. i’m glad i started. i’m glad i kicked myself in the ass when i needed it. and i’m glad i saw the year through.
*
darnell, amir, sala, and i created our visions boards tonight. now we are ready to watch this ball drop with kumani and make 2019 amazing!!
*
happy birthday mommy and happy new year to every single one of you!!!! *
day 365 is in the books...✌🏼

happy new year, my friends. i’m so grateful you are on this journey with me. we struggle, we survive, we thrive. together. ✒🖤 there are too many people to tag, but these are just a few who’ve made it possible for me to dive into this work (and who’ve jumped right into the deep end with me):
.
.
 - logo, creative brand collaboration, pure kindred spirithood, and divine empowerment.

 - new website design and navigation (take a look via link in profile!), ux sanity, a fresh set of eyes, and extreme tolerance for the roller coaster "hey, what if we..." of working with yours truly.

 - poraits that remind me of my capacity to be seen and to experience joy (and the best hugs in the biz). .
.
.
and  - the one who makes me possible, the one who - when i worry i’m not pulling my weight in the busy everyday of our home and family and marriage and life - reminds me that this work is exactly where i need to be, and exactly what i need to be doing.

tag someone you’re grateful for, drop a note about anything you want to say, and get ready for the first  prompt on january 6!

 .

text:
2018 had amazing highs and deep lows! i attended my first book signing which happened to be for #anamericanmarriage by @tayari. i watched as my tiny dancers performed my choreography in my first dance recital as a dance teacher. i self-published my first novel #blueeyes. i publicly shared my own #metoo stories for the first time. i became a supervisor at the day job. i celebrated my 10 year college reunion at #pvhc2k18. i also started going back to therapy. and... i saw @michelleobama in person at #becoming #anintimateconversationwithmichelleobama.
#blackpanther was everything and more. i'm thankful for @drake "i'm upset" video because i was a huge #degrassi fan. i'm also grateful for the #guardiansofthegalaxy movies because i was late to the party but binged over the summer and loved each one. did i mention #blackpanther in all it's awesomeness? 
i lost 20 pounds on #keto and gained it back when i stopped due to high cholesterol. 
i thought i was in love, went crazy, realized i wasn't, and got my shit together. 
what a wild and crazy year!
cheers to 2019 because i'm ready!
#goodbye2018 #welcome2019 #newyearseve

text: happy new years eve to all. ending the year with a strong intention for focusing on gratitude each and everyday going into 2019. i’m most grateful for these two who quite frankly keep breath in my lungs each and every day. don’t know where i’d be without them ❤️ have a safe night as you celebrate the changing of years, be kind to people - those you love and those that are strangers. but most of all try and be kind to yourself. year in and year out - this last part continues to be the most difficult for me. i plan on spending 2019 practicing better psycho-spiritual hygiene and cleaning out the almost 38 years of negative mental and emotional buildup that i’ve been working on accumulating. i’m sure i’ll have set backs and stumbling blocks but i’m going to try to be nice to myself about them instead of letting them cripple my progress.  #pmaalltheway #pma #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness

text:
goodbye to 2018, and hello 2019! 
this year alone gave me some of the biggest challenges in my life, and everyday i am blessed with the endurance to keep on going regardless of the pain and scars i have endured. i honestly will not be missing you at all 2018, but i sure as hell am thankful for the lessons i have learned from it. from getting out of a long term relationship, to treating a tumor, to monitoring a growth on my cholecyst, to rejecting treatments, to a sexual assault, to another chronic disease, to a failing medical system, to being a statistic, to being dehumanized, to the daily challenges of managing my mental health, to borderline alcoholism, to nearly dropping out of college, to cutting out negative relationships in my life, to a miscarriage, and still having the ability to manage surviving through it all. although 2018 has been shit, shit is fertilizer, and i’ve learned to grow through what i’ve gone through. i learned the most about myself, about defining my own happiness, about learning to take control of uncontrollable situations, and love myself even when it was hard to look at who that woman was staring back in the mirror. 2019, please be good to me! i small kind need a break #newyearseve #2019goals #survival #endurance #thisismentalhealth #kintsugi #ptsd #depression #si #anxiety #ocd #add #substanceuse #metoo #sexualassault #sexualviolence #trauma #miscarriageawareness #mylifemyrules #thisispublichealth #growth

text:
we could argue that this video clip and the event that it documents are in no way a highlight of 2018.  i agree that it's a pretty sensational story, but it highlights the realities that working women, especially young ones face each day. 
what makes this unique is that, at least in my experience, the offenders are not usually held accountable.  in 2018 though there were two very public cases where men inappropriately touched waitstaff, their actions were caught on video, and they were prosecuted. 
the service industry has struggled to tackle sexual harassment even as the #metoo movement has prompted changes in other fields. in interviews with the new york times, more than 60 servers and bartenders shared stories of crude comments and harassment they faced from patrons. they spoke of having to decide where to draw the line, and how that affected how much they made in tips. “we deal with a lot,” ms. holden said, referring to female workers who have been groped. she said she knew that she would have the support of the pizzeria’s owners and her co-workers after taking the man down, so she was never afraid of repercussions.

we appreciate that ms. holden felt supported by her employer and would like to point out that employers are responsible for harassment that is perpetrated against their employees in the course of performing their jobs under title vii of the civil rights act of 1964. 
as for ms. holden, “i’m just happy that he was held accountable,” she said. “and i’m very happy that there have been so many women empowered by all of this.” #eeoc #titlevii  #metoo #timesup  #womensmarch #peace #humanrights #womensempowerment #womenempowerment

what makes this unique is that, at least in my experience, the offenders are not usually held accountable.  in 2018 though there were two very public cases where men inappropriately touched waitstaff, their actions were caught on video, and they were prosecuted. 
the service industry has struggled to tackle sexual harassment even as the  movement has prompted changes in other fields. in interviews with the new york times, more than 60 servers and baenders shared stories of crude comments and harassment they faced from patrons. they spoke of having to decide where to draw the line, and how that affected how much they made in tips. “we deal with a lot,” ms. holden said, referring to female workers who have been groped. she said she knew that she would have the suppo of the pizzeria’s owners and her co-workers after taking the man down, so she was never afraid of repercussions.

we appreciate that ms. holden felt suppoed by her employer and would like to point out that employers are responsible for harassment that is perpetrated against their employees in the course of performing their jobs under title vii of the civil rights act of 1964. 
as for ms. holden, “i’m just happy that he was held accountable,” she said. “and i’m very happy that there have been so many women empowered by all of this.”

text:
dear 2018,
wow, you were shitty.
i started off by being taken advantage of by a shitty job that took me for granted and overworked me to the point of hospitalization. i ended a relationship with a guy i'm still lucky enough to call my best friend. i was sexually harassed at the same workplace and put through the humiliating experience of investigation only to have nothing happen.
well, not nothing, i got bullied by hr and my coworkers until i quit.
and then i was preyed on by a man who saw that i was vulnerable and thought that he could take advantage by pressuring me to sleep with him.
i have been ill, i have fought with my past, i have doubted myself. i have rarely felt more alone...
but i also have come to know new and wonderful people, seen beautiful things, nurtured new life in to this world, and created things that bring myself and others joy.
i felt like i was lost in the dark for a long time, and sometimes i still lose my way. but i have learned that the dark is not a frightening place; it is a place where we can retreat to heal, to be nurtured, to find things that cannot be seen.
and if we allow our eyes to adjust, to wait quietly and fight the urge to panic and light a match, we just might find our way amongst the stars.
so here's to 2019, to honoring the darkness within us, and to embracing our power so that we might never be taken advantage of again.
• • •

text:
happy new years. i wanted this photo to encompass who i really am; a giant dork with terrible anxiety who adores horror, fall, and halloween.

i've been very quiet this year about my personal life. i'm worried to do this post now because i am not looking for pity but perhaps understanding and a way to improve myself.

i kept my personal life from the majority of the people i love in my life because i so desperately did not want to be a burden. this year was one of the most difficult i've ever faced. i will not be naming others due to respect for them so please show the same level of respect. also for anything i didn't tell you in person please understand it wasn't you it was me. 
almost a year ago i quit my day job and to that i still have no regrets. i've worked 2 to 3 jobs for 12 years and needed a break. this american grind is bullshit the rich sell us so they can remain lazy and rich. 
i lost a lot this year. i lost weight for one. that part was a highlight because i finally felt healthy. i lost a relationship i thought would last a life time. i attempted my first truly poly relationship to extremely mixed understandings. i lost trust. in myself and in others. someone extremely close to my daughter and i was arrested and that shook myself, my mother and my daughter to our core. i was lied too. i was cheated on multiple times too a depth that was sickening and profoundly hurt me. i lost self confidence due to someone else's pain that i was caught in. i lost sight of myself due to gaslighting. i lost a pregnancy. one i didn't even know i had due to being on strict birth control. a birth control that makes you only have a period once every 3 months so i had no idea. i went to a client's fitting during the process because my overwhelming need to not let others down can sometimes push into an unhealthy area. i lost sleep. i lost my ability to be comfortable in crowds, even of my dearest friends. i lost control of my health mentally and physically. i lost the majority of my blood family and that was by choice and purely freeing. that cut a toxicity that had held me down my whole life.

continued in comments

text:
2018
een jaar met vele mooie gebeurtenissen, waarvan eindreis wel een van de hoogtepunten is. 9 dagen door italië met de zotste (jawel ja zeker wel) maar ook de liefste mensen. bonden met de leerkrachten ( i luuuuuve you tommeke en u ook hoor gigi maar net iets minder) een paar mislukte pisa foto's maken en gondelen op het o zo lekker ruikende water van venetië (aroma's aroma's). daarna kwam het kot leven, grote aanpassing, 1 keer deftig eten maken en iedereen zit foto's te trekken om trots thuis te laten weten da we ook wel eens iets deftig eten op kot. af en toe eens zottekes doen in onze onesie me een pizzake dabei. tog maar besloten om mij te laten dopen bij de beste vereniging ooit #retabo #🖤💛🖤 #alleenmaarlove #geenspijt. nieuwe ontdekkingen doen gelijk de moose bar. tmoeten ni altijd tds in de prof, den boesj of de planeet zijn he. 2018 was ook een jaar waarin er ineens veel verkeersborden in onze keuken bleken te staan en een jaar dat een mooie afsluiter had door ons kerstfeestje en natuurlijk de wereldberoemde retabo kerst td en ook veeeeeeele andere zatte avonden waarop van alles gebeurde maar waarvan de foto's niet voor publicatie vatbaar zijn #oepss #muile
dankjewel 2018 voor de mooie momenten en dankjewel aan alle lovely people die op maar ook degene di ni op de foto's staan want i luuuve you all

text:
new year’s eve is a shitty day for me. 
trigger post..
seven years ago i was sexually assaulted. 
i was passed out drunk, and can only remember bits of it. which i am quite thankful for. 
swab test confirmed and i was driven to put him behind bars. to make him feel humiliated like i did.
i lost friends, received threats and someone egged my mother’s house.
i was called a slut, attention whore, and jealous. the list goes on. 
he told the judge i enticed him. 
when i lost the court case due to lack of evidence to prove it was not consensual; i became depressed, and contemplated ending my life. 
this shit still bothers me, the fact that i almost let him win. 
after realizing i needed change, i packed up and moved 3700km away by myself. 
i didn’t move on, but i’m at peace with it. i still think about it frequently since i feel like i had no closure. 
an important person in my life said “we don’t have to get over things that happened to us” and i couldn’t have heard that at a better time. 
i debated telling this story on my ig since this is my ‘mom’ account but i have a daughter who will eventually know what happened to me. and telling my story through you is going to help me get there. 
if you’ve gotten this far, thank you. 
#metoo #metoomovement #speakout #survivor #assaultsurvivor #raw #rawmotherhood #raisingstronggirls #raisingstrongwomen #empoweringwomen #womenempoweringwomen

text:
here i am. #nomakeup #nofilter just me. 
i have one resolution for 2019, and it’s to love myself and be unapologetic for who i am and what i want out of life. i’ve spent far too long making people a priority who only see me as an option. i’ve apologized when i knew i wasn’t wrong. i endured abuse because i thought as long as my kids were safe, that’s all that mattered.

so under my umbrella resolution, i am committed to the following 10 commandants that will help me live out this resolution. —-
1. i will always remember that my #integrity can only be given away, not taken. 
2. i will enjoy the #littlethings because they are fleeting. 
3. i will own my body because it is mine and only mine. #mybodymychoice 
4. i will love every single scar, stretch mark, and imperfection because they tell #mystory and it’s one i’m proud of. 
5. i will #neversettle by allowing people in my life who will use me.
6. if i allow you into my life, it is a privilege that i gave you and i am in control to take it away. 
7. i will #live and #love guiltlessly and shamelessly. 
8. i will do the things that make me #happy, from taking long runs to eating extra cookies. 
9. i have found #myvoice and i will use it to #inspire others to find and use theirs. 
10. i’ve survived to this point, but this year i will not just survive; i will #thrive. —-
here’s to a fresh start, closing chapters, and a journey of self love i’m so excited to embark on. ❤️ #lovethyself #selfcare #selflove #metoo #strongwomen #womenempowerment #newyearseve #resolutions #2019 #nofilterneeded #lifeisgood #mom #singlemom #youarebeautiful #youareabadass #youareenough 🙌🙌🙌

text:
i was working on this one during the kavanaugh hearings in september. i remember going into work sitting in front of my computer watching the hearings, and crying all day as she gave her testimony. in absolute disbelief that dr. blasey ford had risked so much, finding herself in the crosshairs of her past. she had sacrificed the safety of her family, and endured public and national scrutiny. while judge kavanaugh exhibited behavior one would have expected of an adolescent in a fraternity...living a legacy of privilege and bad behavior (understatement). regardless of the outcome, she was the woman of the year that stood out the most for me. i think dr. ford unknowingly continued to fuel the fire in the hearts of women who have been mistreated and abused for all the reasons that the #metoo movement exists. i'm pretty sure history will be more kind to her than him.
18” x 20” collage and acrylic on museum board | available...i named this one “dr. ford”

text:
since it's new years eve i was going to write something generic about being thankful for all of the pain and struggle i have been put through this year and how it made me a stronger, better person. but truthfully, am i supposed to thank my rapist for making me a better person? am i supposed to be grateful for the rape and say it made me stronger? i'm honestly tired of the "what doesn't kill you makes you stronger" mentality. what does this tale of perseverance say to our rapists? that we have them to thank for our courage and our survivor mentality? that they have gifted us the ability to transcend adversity and find healing. no. the grit and courage i embody existed prior to being assaulted my growth, perseverance and resilience is due to countless hours of hard work in therapy, writing and introspection. being raped did not make me stronger. i became stronger despite being raped.

but considering i don't want my rape and the aftermath to consume my entire vision of this year, i decided to take time to reflect on this painful year regardless of the emotions that surfaced and allow myself to dig deep. 
so here it goes. here are some things i discovered this year:

this blog! i started this page feeling so utterly alone and isolated from everyone. i have used this page to document my growth and case, explore my emotions around my rape, and form meaningful connections with other survivors. this page even led to me being a published poet in amy turberville's poetry collection "wildflower warriors: poetry for a cause." this year has fostered a relationship with writing and poetry and made me a better writer. i have been more raw and vulnerable in my writing than i ever thought i would be, especially considering i am posting many of my writings on the internet.

i gave myself permission to breakdown and fall apart countless of times. i am a fiercely independent person and for me breaking down meant losing the only thing i felt i knew about myself. i gained strength in rebuilding myself from the most bare essence of who i am.

are any of you in the same position as you reflect on 2018?
comment a ❤ below if you read this far.

text:
(< 1 min read): 2018 has been an amazing year filled with love, laughs and a fair share of challenges. whew! i got married and officially became a mother. we bought a house and i started a business—the woke coach. .
i am thankful for my family (near and far) and the many blessings that god has sent our way. .
i’m happy that the woke coach has allowed me to use my voice in a way i never thought possible and it’s been amazing! .
i was on the radio: i partnered with kerri miller and @mprnews to curate and facilitate conversations on identity: #metoo and making allies. i also appeared on @899kmoj on the african american forum with sylvia bartley to talk about black women, self care and the #metoo movement— twice! 
i traveled: i visited san francisco, las vegas, new york city, los angeles, new orleans and portland for work and i went to the dominican republic, boston and san diego just for fun! 
i volunteered: i helped raise nearly $1 million for arts education programs at the @walkerartcenter through avant garden and helped find the new director! i co-chaired the after party experience committee for the @guthrietheater gala and served on the fellow travelers task force to bring the diversely cast @mnopera production to every-body. 
i worked: major love to #artequity, new england foundation for the arts, mn theater alliance (to name a few). .
.
most importantly, i worked on me: i participated in a few professional development opportunities (s/o to @forecastpublicart, leadership twin cities, and @bushfoundation and independent sector). i received my idi certification and a “train the trainer” certificate from the university of mn. and i found time to get regular massages and reiki sessions. yasss!! .
.
i made a ton of wonderful new friends who made me laugh and cry laughing! .
and thank you to my day one’s that held me down all year no matter what. i love you! .
.
in 2019, i want to read more, be the healthiest version of myself (i.e. less wine, more yoga, and more self care), be braver than i've ever been and live by the mantra, “if it’s not a hell yes, then it’s a no. period! .
.
happy new year! i certainly hope our paths cross. 😊
.
#2019 #happynewyear #thewokecoach

text:
“in japan, when a piece of pottery breaks, some potters fill the cracks with gold. the potters, they see the repairs as something beautiful. they know that the unexpected happens. change happens. they know that nobody gets through this world in one piece. but that doesn’t have to diminish us. the cracks are part of our history. they will always be with us. they made us better. they made us stronger. they made us something new.” -grey’s anatomy 
2018 was a year i put a lot of faith into. i was hopeful for many things, some of which didn’t happen. rather, it was extremely hard. heartbreak. depression. lots of changes. being sexually assaulted a week before my new program. a scary medical diagnosis of someone really close to me. losing my grandma. dealing with the repercussions of ptsd in various ways. gaining more weight than i’d like to admit and feeling completely helpless in my body for many reasons. 2018, you were very painful, but i know one day i’ll realize that you were a necessary chapter in my life. no, nothing is magically healed, but my perspective on life has surely shifted. 
so while i usually loathe new years eve wishes (given that it’s arguably my least favorite day of the year), i choose to reclaim it this year. 2019, you are the year of getting back to me, getting to a healthy level of self-love that i had never reached before. regaining the parts of me that felt broken and shattered and piecing them back together with gold ♥️ some things i wish for one day might be put on hold, waiting for the right time, but for now, i’m learning to be okay with the process, okay with myself and where i’m at, and okay with healing every part of me. 
thank you all for the love and support. for those who don’t have a super positive “2018 was wonderful!!” post, it’s okay. this is life. it’s real, raw and ugly at times. you are seen and loved. #resilience #metoo #believesurvivors #singlegirl #trusttheprocess #survivor #gradschool #slpgradstudent #slp2b #linguist2clinician #healing #2019 #newversionsofme #happynewyear #newperspectives #yearofme #greysquotes

text:
i raise my fist to change! as the clock ticks down on another year, i raise my fist to all the women who have fought back in 2018. i raise my fist to shattering the glass ceiling. i raise my fist to time's up. i raise my fist to #metoo. i raise my fist to feminism. i raise my fist to diversity and inclusion. 
2018 has been a landslide of change and i believe it to be only the beginning. i know for a fact we are a long way from being a united race. we as humans should strive to treat one another with compassion and humility no matter an individual's circumstance, position, background, skin color, religion, identification, anything! we as people should strive to empower each and every person to do their best and be their best! 
i'm here fighting along side every person facing any sort of battle. whether it be internal or external. i will continue to fight for equality and the fundamental right to be human. 
here's to 2019, where i will continue killing people with kindness ✌🏽 #onerace #human #newyear #sameme

text:
in january i set my yearly reading goal - in 2018 i would read 20 books. by march, i noticed that i had begun the year with five books written by female authors. for some reason, this was slightly shocking to me. why did it feel like this was so unusual? it was then that i came to the full realization of how male-dominated my literary life was growing up — in high school you read “the greats”: george orwell, f. scott fitzgerald, john steinbeck, william shakespeare, j.d. salinger, mark twain, kurt vonnegut. while in theory i had later come to understand there were, of course, so many more “greats”, it was time to truly consider how reading a multitude of words penned by old (dead) white men framed the way i saw the world. spurred on by this thought, and the #metoo movement, i set out to complete my reading goal, but focused solely on books written by, and about, strong women. around june, i realized this must be what reading was like for men the majority of the time — the solace you experience by seeing integral aspects your life echoed and reimagined by someone who fully understands the fundamentals of you. 
here’s to 2019 - may it bring you a more complete sense of self, light in the darkness, and love and laughter wherever you can find it.

a big thank you to @ashleyspivey and #spiveys📚club for the many recommendations, and reigniting my passion for reading.

my top five books read in 2018: 
1) #homegoing by #yaagyasi
2) #thedinnerlist by @rebecca_serle 
3) #weshouldallbefeminists by @chimamanda_adichie 
4) #smallgreatthings by @jodipicoult 
5) #thekissquotient by @hhoangwrites 📸: @stlartmuseum

text:
now their are a lot of things most people don't know about me... examples - i was a muslim in the past but not anymore, or i support lgbtq+ and human rights for all, also many more things. but these are just to name a few! i have received a lot of threats and some were death threats, from people mainly because i left my islamic faith (it's a personal choice i made and i wish people would respect that!) and i also received a lot of bullying, and i was abused quite a lot when i was younger and the fact that my father is not the best person he could be just made it even worst. so many people are against me because i am willing to speak up and stand up for what is right, like take islam for example many people will call me an islamaphobe (which to them the meaning is i hate islam, it's basically the same as being homophobic but towards islam) and that's not true, but yet people will say i am. i just want to let everyone know that you don't have to be scared to *speak up* you have as much rights as everyone else does, now i am not asking you to get violent or take it too far, but say something and you should be allowed to say something. if you can't have these simple rights and normal things in life like freedom of speech or freedom in general and what you want to do in your life, then that's not humanity. 2018 was the big year, it was a year where i became more aware and changed my perspective and outlook on life. it was hard to change at first and i endured a lot of hardship, well we all do let's be honest. but this year everything is going to change. i am going be proud of myself, stop blaming myself and stop being afraid to have these simple things in life such as freedom, human rights etc... i hope you will not be afraid too 🤗😌😊
*

text:
philwen and pbcwe wish you and your loved ones a (belated) merry christmas and a happy new year. 
this season, we take time to reflect on how our partnerships have paved the way forward in making the workplace more inclusive by challenging traditional beliefs, breaking barriers, and eliminating gender stereotypes. •

we thank our governing council members: accenture, ayala (and ayala land inc), convergys (now concentrix), magsaysay group, natasha, sgv & co., and ssi group for their strong support and commitment to institutionalizing workplace gender equality and to influence their networks and supply chains to follow suit. •

this year, we welcome our new member and partner, insular life, and we look forward to working with other filipino companies who will also lead the gender equality advocacy in their respective industries. •

we approach the new year full of hope and excitement and we want to thank you for you unyielding commitment in the values that the business coalition represent. •

happy new year!

this year, we welcome our new member and partner, insular life, and we look forward to working with other filipino companies who will also lead the gender equality advocacy in their respective industries. •

we approach the new year full of hope and excitement and we want to thank you for you unyielding commitment in the values that the business coalition represent. •

happy new year!

text:
2018 -mourned the state of the highest office in the land
-celebrated both parents turning 80
-traverse city with “the girls”
-celebrated in-laws 60th wedding anniversary
-celebrated my baby’s graduation from high school
-appreciated the love and support of dear friends
-hugged friends tightly as their parents passed away
-celebrated weddings and births
-watched my children continue to grow into adulthood ❤️
-bought a third car
-#metoo
-voted
-experienced more change at work, missed working with excellent therapists and then was delighted to have them replaced by excellent therapists and old friends became new again -made new connections and new friends
-re-connected with college “honorary” family and got to catch up with them and get to know their spouses for the first time.
-saw a forever friend
-adopted a dog, fell in love with her
-traveled across the state with my girl looking at colleges
-all girl family spa weekend
-felt grief over the death of an old friend
-celebrated the new year!

text:
looking back on my journal entries this year. what a beautiful year it’s been. thank you thank you thank you 🌸
.
1/11/18 “ i want to go back and just give young anntherese a hug and say it’s going to be okay, stop running! i knew what to do but i didn’t. now i’m going to 💛”
.
1/28/18 “i feel so sad. today is the first day i’ve spent entirely alone in a long time.”
.
5/31/18 “i look back now at everything and see so much  beauty in the things i didn’t put much thought into...”
.
6/1/18 “dragonflies were all around me, there wasn’t a cloud in the sky. something tells me this day is just for me. i’m so happy to be alive. i’m so happy to be connected”
.
9/1/18 “i love you and all the crazy beautiful parts of you. please keep vibin’, don’t give up 💛”
.
11/5/18 “i feel so foolish”
.
11/27/18 “i am a survivor.”
.
11/29/18 “i am my savior”
.
12/6/18 “i want strangers to meet me and feel joy. i want them to feel a presence of love. i want them to feel free. i want them to feel all this because that’s what i am, that’s what we all are 💛”
#reflecting #newyear #thankful #journal #contemplating #vulnerability #source #love #light #itsokaytobesad #youaretheuniverse #thebeautyineverything #selflove #free #metoo #survivor

text:
y'all 2018 was rough on me. i spent the first week of the new year in the hospital. 
had two surgeries. two major injuries. a chest infection post pacemaker surgery. my grandfather died. and as of nov. 28th #metoo is now a part of my story. i'm not sharing this to get sympathy. but to say that i'm still standing. i'm still blessed. i'm still here. i am worn out, i am scarred, i am exhausted. i am drained emotionally. but this year didn't break me. my grandmother used to always say we give out but we don't give up. that has helped me through the last part of this year in particular. and it will be a driving force behind my 2019. #sharelove #it'sokaynottobeokay #newyearnewchapter

text:
2018 was an introspective year, filled with exploring, reflecting, and sharing without attachment to “successful” outcomes. i dabbled in art, in writing, in photography, and in music and somehow still kept my day job. i created 100+ art pieces, got paid for my photography, wrote 11 original songs, learned a new instrument, and wrote my first episode of tv. ▫️
that all to say, i also faced a lot of rejection, constantly questioned if i was doing the right things for myself and my future, felt loneliness in my first few months living alone, addressed trauma i didn’t realize was trauma, and had some of the most heart-wrenching breakthroughs with new friends, old friends, and other loved ones about mental health, loss, spirituality, and #metoo. ▫️
2018 was beautiful and weird and regardless of whether any of these projects see the light of day, i created things that helped me prove to myself that i’m capable of a little more than i thought. above all else, i’m consistently grateful for the strength of my inner circle... the most supportive group of people constantly inspiring and encouraging me, by the things they say and do, the way they live their lives, countering any reason for me to doubt myself.
▫️
lessons learned: think less and act when inspiration hits. trust your gut. make things even if they’re shit. listen to your friends & family... unless they’re wrong 🤷🏽‍♀️😂 (jk love y’all)... happy new year!

text:
happy 2019!!!
•
if you're dedicated to building a life you truly deserve in 2019, believe me when i say, "it starts with you!"
•
what does that mean?
•
simple. you can't expect change if you keep doing everything the same.
•
change means you have to strip away all your beliefs, and start over.
•
to do that, you need to understand those beliefs in the first place.
•
this is what i do. it's what i did to heal from my 10 years of child abuse. and it's what i teach my clients who are ready for real change.
•
if you're ready, i'm here for you. click the link in my bio and book your free discovery call to discuss how my survivor to warrior coaching program will change your life.
•
•
#metoo #changeyourthoughts #changeyourlife #survivor #believeinyourself

text:
i’m going to be honest here, new years, has lost all its meaning. its become a day where you go to a party and get drunk, post videos of yourself screaming at midnight, and making resolutions you don’t plan on keeping. the day of “new year, new me” while continuing with the same old bullshit. so let’s change that. new years is about reflecting on your past year, no matter how good or bad. finding out why it was so bad so you can make changes next year & vice versa; why it was good, so you can continue that behaviour. it’s about changing your attitude; it a fresh start, so start off positive. set reasonable resolutions; it’s better to have small goals & reach them than make impossible ones & hate yourself when you can’t complete them. and as you’re reflecting, if you realize that you didn’t like this year, feel no obligation to look for the silver lining. “the good in the bad”. if this year was the worst for you, use it to make 2019 better. new years is a reason to have a fresh start, not a reason to party till you knock out. here’s to new memories, opportunities, people, and wiping the slate clean. cheers 🥂💓 ~ musk •
•
•

text: it’s the end of the year and i just want to say i’m so proud of all of you for surviving. in the beginning of january 2018 i almost killed myself because i thought the flashbacks and memories of the assault would never go away and at the time, i truly believed i would never get better. it’s been a year now, and thankfully, i can say i was wrong. i’m so incredibly happy now and thankful i didn’t kill myself when i wanted to. to all of you survivors, please hang on because i promise i gets better. i know that in the moment it’s hard to believe, trust me, i’ve been there but it will get better and i believe in you! i love you all so much and again, i’m so proud of you. ❤️ -rissy  #love #youareenough #loveyourselffirst #quotes #quotesdaily #inspiration #sexualassault #empowerment  #survivor #metoo #metoomovement #recovery #feminist #feminism #feministquote  #trauma #female #inspirationalquote #equality #trigger #triggerwarning #assault #ptsd #mybodymychoice #consent #endrapeculture #timesup #depression #anxiety

text:
another amazing #nsng transformation to closeout 2018. this update is from april 2018 from cortney suderman. swipe right to left for more fun pics. 
here is her story @csuds27 : 
i was an athlete growing up and even managed to make the cut walking on to a d1 college rowing team. once a was done with college the weight piled on easily. i was up and down and then back up plus an extra few, for years i went through this cycle. i have tried every fad diet out there, and i mean everything and always with eventual failure. skip ahead a few more years and two kids later and i was an overweight mom. i hated what i had become but mostly hated what i was now modeling for my kids. i wanted them us to be an adventurous family, i wanted them to be outdoors and love activity.

when i found nsng through the first “carolla effect” i was broken. @adamcarolla mentally, physically, and metabolically. i never truly weighed in at first because i was to scared to see he numbers but i know i was around 215 pounds. i am 5’5” so that was not a good thing. 
today i am healthy and strong. i weigh 155, give or take a couple, very consistently. more importantly i am myself again! i have learned to love running and have gotten back into triathlon. i’ve even tried new things like trail running. this last year i ran my first full marathon, multiple shorter races, completed a sprint tri, and an 18 and 20 mile trail race! in a couple weeks i will be trying for my first 50k. i am now in the body that my ambitious mind deserves and i cannot thank you enough for showing me he way!!! before pic: 
size 14 
after pic: 
size 4-6 april 2018
another after:
during my last 20 mile trail race, what i now consider life in to living!

thank you from the bottom of my heart! you have changed my life and my family’s life!
.
.
.
#bodytransformation #nosugar #nograins #transformation #trailrunning

text:
i mean... i guess i laughed a little bit? mostly because asians are routinely ignored in almost every industry especially comedy. we were neither embraced as comedians nor considered subject matter other than portraying us as stereotypes. so thanks for the shout-out. 
this douchebag predator went from the genius horace & pete to a new peak with his netflix special to being outed as a piece of shit deviant to this hacky material not even worthy of a firehouse.

he was the comedian that offended but did it right. he was my new howard stern. absurdist. king of irony. he seemed like an ally of the lgbt community and helped us laugh at privileged straight white men through self-deprecation. he even made liberal people question their own internalized racism with his jokes.

now the nail is in the coffin. his core fans are gone and most of his comedian buddies have distanced themselves. and if they hadn't before, they're openly shunning him now.

so move over louis because we have pamela adlon, hannah gadsby, sarah silverman, chelsea peretti, chris rock, patton oswald, fred armisen and a slew of young comics to take the spotlight. he's out of touch, out of material and certainly out of gusto. there's no outrage. it's more of a disappointment. good riddance. 
#louisck
#metoo

at the end of july of this year i was raped by 2 guys. it was horrible. and i have flashbacks to that night all the time. i felt disgusting and it broke me in ways i didn’t know possible. it was the most traumatic experience i have ever been through. and after i isolated myself from everyone. i still am not even close to being 100%. i fight everyday with the demons inside of me. and i struggle to find the strength most days to get up and smile. but i’m trying. and i will keep trying. every day i become stronger. and i hope that 2019 will bring much more joy to my life than 2018. because 2018 has left me in a million pieces that i’m struggling to put back together.

that’s the reason i picked up and moved to austin.

i know im not alone in these experiences which makes it even worse. i feel bad for all the girls who have to wake up and feel the way that i do everyday. but we will make it. #metoo #depression

skipping ahead a bit to #2012. v was around 6 months old when we decided to buy a 38’ class a, diesel rv. we called her butterface. she was lovely on the inside, but her face....well....her face had seen better days. that summer, we packed up the crew and went on a 5,000 mile eastern and midwestern us road trip. this is what it looks like to hike with a fat baby and four lazy chihuahuas. this is also what it looks like when you cut your own hair in an rv mirror and instantly have regrets about that decision.

text:
the time i realized the power of saying hello...
.
.
people often say it’s hard to say goodbye but that’s never been the case for me.  i’m pretty good at saying bye to a lot of things, a lot of people, a lot of experiences.  throughout my lifetime i’ve ghosted friendships, partners, jobs, places, and even some family.  nah...i’m pretty good at saying bye.  what i’m not good at is saying hello to all that’s coming to me.
.
.
you see i’m good at saying bye to things, people, and circumstances because i use to stuff things deep in the dark holes of my mind where i can never see it or think about it again...ever.  or so i thought.  in 2018 those things, those people, that past i use to stuff has found it’s stubborn way to pop up in my life...and it wasn’t pretty...it was pretty savage.  all of it popped up in my relationships, in me being a father, at work, in music, in my everyday. .
.
so maybe 2019 is the year i learn to say hello...hello to all the things, people, and past that i still need to meet head-on and deal with.  no more stuffing...no more acting like they don’t exist...no more letting it pop up unexpectedly in my relationships or in my life.  and maybe that’s the trick...maybe i need to learn to say hello to dealing with my stuff...all of it...all the things, people, and the past.  because maybe when i do i can also learn to say hello to the life i wanna have...the life i’m meant to lead...the man i know i can be.  maybe.  #imabeautifulmess 💜🤴🏾💯
.
p/s...happy new year...i hope y’all know you are worth it, you are beautiful, you are powerful! 💪🏾✨💯
.
.

text:
my boots keeps on bouncing me to 2019. 
2018 has been an amazing year to me! incredible, learning and so many wonderful opportunity. 
i came, i saw and i learned... in this 2018 i was on a paper three times in one month. i became a u.s citizen after many years of waiting and crying and some other days that i thought i was going to give up and loose myself, but i have wonderful and amazing people surrounding me, that they gave me support that i needed and encouraged me on my way to get there...
this year came to me with so many surplices, ups and downs, rains and sunshine’s... part of 2018 knocked me down but i didn’t stay down there ratter i did stand up and sake if off and kept moving forward because that’s what we all do, because there is alway hope..., it also gave me some lemons and i turned them to lemoned and enjoyed my drink... there was times that i felt like i was lonely walking in the middle of nowhere, where my life journey seamed not having a start and end, i felt like i was in a tunnel that never had the light on the end of it... but most of all, i’m loving my journey of coming into my own self, even more. 
my faith, my family, my family home and away from home, my friends and my work they kept me going, they all gave me a reason to smile and to push forward so that i can keep on enjoying the america dream, that’s when i found my purpose.
2018 i gained one year in my life and this coming 2019 i’m looking forward into one more and many more to come. for me age brings with it an increased self awareness, decreased concern about what others think and enhanced focus on the things that matters to me. 
in this evolution of life that have seen many things changing from women gaining their power politics, #metoo movement also came and women became fearless and that’s the america i need to to live in and have a voice too... i won’t shy back and din my light.

instead, i will roar, i will hike, i will run and staying health this is my goal this coming year 2019... unapologetically. i am enjoying and ‘becoming’... and as long as my journey continues... may this be so because this is who i am and this is me. 
goodbye 2018. you were fast and fabulous!

text: to put it simply 2018 was a shit show. i lost friends, i was betrayed, assaulted, and hurt, and i lost myself. i went into such a dark place and didn’t see a light and thought there was no way out. it started getting a bit better after i had began going to therapy but then something major happened. i was raped. it’s really hard for me to come out and say this but i’m sick and tired of feeling ashamed for something that wasn’t my fault. i have suffered from depression and anxiety for many years and this incident really pushed me over the edge. i had no motivation for anything and struggled to get out of bed every morning if i even did. but as the year comes to an end i can confidently say that this has not defined me. i am not a victim i am a survivor. and with the support of friends and family i have moved past one of the biggest obstacles in my life. it will always be a part of me and a part of what has shaped me as a person. and i just want to say if anyone has gone through a similar experience i am always here to talk. i know how lonely it can feel. and even if you haven’t been through what i have i’m willing to talk about anything or just simply give resources. no one deserves to suffer alone. #metoo

text:
fearlessness. 
i’ve adopted this word as my motto. i look to this word for courage. it’s inscribed on the necklace that i never remove.
2018 was a very full year. it seems that more happened in this year than 365 days should allot. mostly, this year has been consumed with eye opening events, led by fearless individuals, and the beginning of dearly needed change. -as a teacher, watching @marchforourlives gave me immense hope for school safety changes. -witnessing dr. christine blasey ford speak her truth in front of the nation was nothing less than awe inspiring. -knowing the powerful men of hollywood finally met the punishment for their crimes proved how much the #metoo movement can accomplish, and how a voice can prompt change. -seeing mariska hargitay and the joyful heart foundation continue to bring light to the rape kit backlog gave me hope, and that hope continues to grow with their continued commitment. 
so many powerful and inspiring things happened this year. 2019 will only continue to bring change. this i believe. 
#2018reflection #changes #fearlessness #joyfulheartfoundation #mariskahargitay #marchforourlives #christineblaseyford #metoo #timesup #endthebacklog #rapekitbacklog #iamevidence #thisibelieve 
@iamevidencethemovie @therealmariskahargitay @thejhf

text_retweet:
we are glad to have reached and impacted over 2000 young girls and women in the year 2018 alone and in all our projects and outreaches we discussed some of the following rights of every girl:
.the human right to protection from all physical or mental abuse.
.the human right to protection from economic and sexual exploitation, prostitution, and trafficking.
.the human right to freedom from forced or early marriage.
.the human right to a standard of living adequate for a child's intellectual, physical, moral, and spiritual development.
.the human right to a healthy and safe environment.
.the human right to education at all levels.

and stressed the importance of speaking up, when they know any this is denied.
looking out to reach a larger number of girls in the year 2019
 #repost @equalitynoworg (@get_repost)
・・・
in 2018 women shook the world, and we are ready to do it all over again next year. •••

text:
2018 // the year i self-published a bestselling book (@barenakedbravery), and went on tv to talk about it (@newdaynw) the year i left washington state on a national book tour and ended up moving to nashville, tn. the year i cared for my grandfather in his final months and learned a new way to say goodbye. the year we began to say #metoo and #ibelieveher. the year i found a new echelon of my voice. the year i started @theschoolofbravery for fellow #creativevisionary peeps. the year i heard myself say “never again” and “i deserve more.” the year i relaxed into a new depth of not-yet-understanding and being okay with it. the year i was diagnosed with hypothyroidism, took a lot of naps, and therefore learned how to automate 80% of my business and life out of necessity. the year i competed in and won songwriting competitions. the year i let my hair do what it’s wanted to do for years.
_
here’s to flowing into another year of firsts!

text:
it was 18 photos ago that i posted a photo of henry and i at the beginning of 2018.  i said that my resolution for the year was to “simplify”. i can say, without hesitation, that simplify was on my head and heart everyday of this year.  i cleaned house both literally and figuratively.  my head needed some space so i took time to clear out the garbage that i had been lugging around and fill my mind with love and knowledge.  i read more books this year than i have in the past 10 years (no joke). i listened, observed, and took notes diligently.  i meditated and visualized.  i got to the root of some hurts that had been holding me back for quite sometime.  i was faced with some scary health issues that took a toll on me both physically and mentally.  through the journey of 2018 i never lost focus of my resolution.  simplify.  and that, i did.
❤️ as we close out this year and step into 2019, i feel prepared, ready, and focused for what is next.  i plan to focus on creativity, health, and diligence.  for 2019 my resolution is “diligence” with love, of course!! ❤️ diligence - steady, earnest, persistent, and energetic effort
❤️ i have simplified and prepared.  now, with diligence, i will take action. ❤️ i will be very active here and also on my fashionably dirty platform.  come join me over there as well @fashionablydirty ❤️ happy new year!! #2019withloveanddiligence

text:
as we round out 2018, we are reflecting on the many incredible moments that caused us to pause, stand and celebrate with womxn across the globe. this year, justice was the most searched word and rightly so as women fought hard won battles for equal rights. 
our highlights include: 
1. #metoo - we started the year raising our voices about sexual violence 
2. we saw our political power grow with the election of women of colour in key positions in both canada and the us administration 
3. after many years of advocacy, women in saudi arabia finally have the right to drive - skrrt skrrt 
4. and womxn loving womxn is finally legal in india with the end of the gay sex ban!
we're excited for the possibilities of 2019!
#reflection #womensmovement #solidarity #success #fightforyourrights #fightlikeagirl #lgbtqrights

text:
de um lado, o movimento #metoo, com seu foco no assédio e na violência, deu um novo impulso ao debate global sobre o feminismo, graças, em boa medida, ao ambiente gerado pelas marchas das mulheres e a sua contestação à chegada de donald trump à casa branca.
na américa latina, setores cristãos católicos e evangélicos lançaram uma cruzada contra o que denominam “ideologia de gênero”, que pretende, segundo eles, a homossexualização de meninos e meninas e a depravação. muito ativos em países como peru, equador e colômbia, esses grupos encontraram um porta-voz muito potente no presidente eleito do brasil, jair bolsonaro.
na arábia saudita, enquanto de um lado era suspensa a proibição de mulheres dirigirem, de outro foram presos muitos ativistas que lutavam pelos direitos femininos. o mundo árabe, aliado ao fundamentalismo religioso, sofreu sérios retrocessos na última década.
na rússia, onde mais de 12.000 mulheres morrem por ano vítimas da violência doméstica, uma lei recente redefiniu o próprio conceito de violência: se o abuso não tem como resultado ossos quebrados e não é cometido mais de uma vez por ano, não está sujeito a penas de prisão. no máximo a uma multa de cerca de 500 euros.
para não falar da liberal europa, onde o primeiro-ministro húngaro viktor orbán oferece educação gratuita às mulheres, mas apenas se tiverem pelo menos três filhos; ou na polônia, onde o governo estimula as mulheres a “procriar como coelhos”; ou na itália, onde está sendo elaborada uma lei que permite acusar as mulheres que denunciaram violência doméstica se seus maridos não forem condenados.
é preciso seguir batalhando, tanto de casa como de qualquer esfera pública, para mudar essas mentalidades que ainda pretendem limitar às mulheres, pelo simples fatos de serem mulheres, seu lugar no mundo. este próximo ano de 2019 será outro ano crucial nesse sentido. não se pode dar nem um passo atrás.

text:
“if you do not see her, you have to be her.” are the words i chose to live by in 2018. as i watched the #metoo movement unveil the countless amount of people who are victims of sexual assault, harassment, rape, etc. i couldn’t help but wonder when the conversation was going to be taken a step further.

when do we get to say, “this happened to #metoo and this is what life looks like after?” when do we get to openly share tools, resources, and healing modalities with pride, not shame? 
wanting to run and hide from the internal dialogue, i kept referring back to those words, “#beher.” i'm so glad i chose not to hide! “being her” in 2018 took me on the most magical adventures. i wrote my first amazon best selling book, who will love me? a holistic approach to building meaningful relationships after sexual assault(link below), started my phd, bought my first house, played interim assistant dean, dipped my toes in both the atlantic and pacific, cried tears and then cried more tears, faced my fears, said yes to all the scary things, and found a greater love for myself and others.

bring on 2019!

https://www.amazon.com/who-will-love-meaningful-relationships-ebook/dp/b07h9n6zsl

text: for those of you who don't know, i've struggled with ptsd since being drugged and raped close to 4 years ago. i wanted to share this (as scary as this is) because i'm tired of holding the weight of a shameful secret, a weight that i never asked for. one of my goals for the new year is to let go of fear, and part of that is to not be afraid of having a voice. for me that means not being afraid of vulnerability, of letting myself create art again, of not fading into the background because that feels safer than standing out. i have gotten to the point where i am so tired of being frozen in place. it may be a slow journey to get to this place, but to all you others out there fighting similar fights, we can do this! 🔥#metoo #dontstopfighting

text:
2019 is almost there and one of the questions that go perfectly together with new years eve is: do you have any good resolutions? so let me answer this. yes i have. my aim for the next year is not to accept any sexism and to finally tell people off. unfortunately some people still need a reminder after the #metoo debate. characters on stage have nothing to do with personality and give you no right to treat anyone with disrespect. i won't laugh in a girly shamefull way. i will be proud. i will not hide. i will treat my body with the respect that it deserves. i will not be ashamed. my best friend @_claire.de.lune_ gave me the idea to show you the costumes where i had to suffer stupid comments about my body. i won't tell you the whole story now but i decided to react with pride in 2019. so caution sexists!

text:
as january 1st fast approaches, we're reflecting on highlights from this amazing past year. thanks to your support, we've accomplished so much and served more than 4,500 community members and survivors!
.
our shelter, 24-hour access line, and advocacy center continue to help families find the safety, healing, and independence they deserve. and we launched five innovative new programs, plus a #newwebsite!
.
we’re now offering confidential advocacy at two high schools in partnership with portland public schools (@ppsimages) and at ohsu’s richmond clinic (@ohsunews).
.
our prevention education program has expanded to address and reduce sex trafficking in partnership with @newaves4youth and #calltosafety.
.
our executive director won a stephen b. herrell award for outstanding collaborative efforts to end family violence, our shelter and housing services manager christina mcgovney was a @willametteweek #skidmoreprize finalist.
.
so many beautiful things have happened! and there's still time to support all of this life-saving and life-changing work. it’s easy to make a difference at @raphaelhousepdx via the @giveguide — just click the link in our bio and together we can build a brighter future that’s free from domestic violence.
.

text:
a significant amount of change is taking place here. in the last 6 months things have moved a lot, colonial structures that were under heavy restoration are now housing families. if you go, make sure to get outside the tourist areas. 
this country like many others has a healthy artists community.  most of the serious art here deals with the past and future of cuba, the messaging focused towards cubans home and abroad. 
the last sculpture of the naked woman riding a rooster has been explained two different ways, i am going with this one: in the past there were two places in this world for women, in the kitchen or on a cock. this protest piece is an acknowledgment that the #metoo movement has very old, international roots.

#travel #people #bewoke #beaware  #wethepeople @wecomeasequals #cuba

text:
every new years i say it has been the worst year ever, but 2018 without a doubt takes the cake for the absolute worst year of my life. a terrible car accident  and my baby dude's passing took a toll on me physically, but the main source of my struggles was that 2018 was the year of sexual assault in the media. for almost 5 years i have been burying memories and trying to pretend they never happened to me. all through this year with the times up and me too movements, and the kavanaugh-blasey ford supreme court case being broadcasted everywhere i went, i had no choice but to face my past and stop lying to myself. i have suffered too much to deny it any longer, and i have finally realized i have nothing to be ashamed or embarassed about. my deepest apologies go out to anyone who had to deal with me in my emotional state this year (or the past 5). reliving trauma is no joke and i want to thank all my friends and loved ones who have stuck by me. here's hoping 2019 will be a year of making happy memories, healing and self acceptance. #metoo #timesup #nye2018 .
.
.
these photos feature some of the fun and happy moments that helped me through this year. big thanks to some of my closest peeps for all your love and support always @scatalog @lizard512 @psychedelicnails @therealteridactyl @jaz.gif
