text:
i could write a post about all of my accomplishments, successes, and the highs & lows of 2018. but instead i want to say thank you.
•
thank you to the people, places, spaces, opportunities, mistakes and the heartbreaks that positioned me in a posture to welcome
growth,
grace,
faith,
understanding,
curiosity,
introspection
& compassion.
•
my word for 2018 was home, and although i transcribed that as learning to “come home” to myself in body, mind and spirit...god intended to challenge me further.
•
to uproot my life by moving across the country and leaving the comforts of “home,” has been one of the hardest yet most beautiful seasons. after years of relying on my support system to help me prune and plant fresh seeds to grow, it was time to water on my own. i was forced into a space of necessary isolation & introspection, a space where i could quiet the world and truly listen to & rely on me. no more distractions, no more safety blankets. for that i’m so much more resilient. for that i’m so fucking grateful.
•
although so many what if’s hang in the air, there are a few things i know to be absolutely true. i have clarity that home is much more of a feeling than a thing. for instance: the way i feel about my husband is home. i feel at home when i’m on a stage and challenging the cultural stigmas that kept my story and truth hidden in the shadows for too many years. i feel at home when i’m guiding others who are suffering in silence to freedom from those same stigmatic chains of shame. i feel home when i’m leaning on faith and loving god before myself. home is nowhere, yet everywhere. it’s what we make it. thankful for a year of seeing my version of home with clear eyes. 2018, you were a gem.

text:
fact: 2018 was a steaming pile of shit wrapped inside a nightmare flavored tortilla. - friends died #rip - family died
- work was slow
- two completely psycho relationships with seriously scary people (that’s right... i don’t post about my dating life) - stopped working for or was fired by violent abusive men - #metoo #brettkavanagh #billcosby #kevinspacey & the horrible people who support them - that destroyed my sleep #mentalhealth - #insomnia & all-time lows in #depression & all-time highs in #ptsd #anxiety panic attacks - two #contractors stole thousands of dollars from me & destroyed several rooms in my house, never finishing the work they were hired for before disappearing (& threatening to sue me as icing on the cake)

but it wasn’t all bad... - made some great new friends
- edited #sound @manhattanbeachstudios for @boogalooshrimpdocumentary working with #dance idol @boogalooshrimp2001 - started working for a couple of great people who appreciate me
- #dj amazing #barmitzvah parties all over the country
- rebranded companies with @weddingsbywolfie & @marvelousmitzvahs - officiated some beautiful #wedding
- set a 90 day goal and wrote my first book (first draft, 70,000 words) #writer
- got to serve the #homeless community @laughfactoryhw standing alongside some of the legends of comedy old and new 
so what’s on the horizon:
- perhaps trap some lucky soul with a baby (a guy can dream)
- second draft of my book followed by pro editors & publisher submissions by my agent - getting @krazypopstudio #recordingstudio back up & running after finishing construction for #voiceover & composing - #producer #songwriter #musiclife
- writing a #script for an #animated series and pitch to @adultswim among others
- short #movie i was in coming out soon - working on the standup comedy act - really enjoying that no matter where it leads #comedian
- travel to israel, to japan, and hoping for thailand and australia. 
truly #grateful for those who stuck by my side during some of the darkest times i have experienced. much love & appreciation to you. let’s change the word together in #2019 #happynewyear

text:
jamás permitas que ninguna persona te esclavice; tú naciste para ser una persona amada… no para ser esclava.

jamás permitas que tu corazón sufra en nombre del amor.  amar es un acto de felicidad, no de sufrimiento.

jamás permitas que tus ojos derramen lágrimas por alguien que nunca te hará reír.

jamás permitas que tu cuerpo sea usado; es la morada de tu espíritu y de tu alma. manténlo apreciado.

jamás permitas quedarte horas esperando por alguien que nunca vendrá, aunque te lo tenga prometido.

jamás permitas que tu nombre sea pronunciado en vano por alguien que no vale la pena.

jamás desperdicies tu tiempo con alguien que nunca tendrá tiempo para ti.

jamás permitas que te hablen a gritos.  si te han de hablar, que sea con amor.

jamás permitas que tus pies caminen en dirección de una persona que se la pasa huyendo de ti.

jamás permitas que los sueños de otros se mezclen con los tuyos, tornándolos en una gran pesadilla.

jamás permitas vivir angustiada en la dependencia de alguien, haciéndote creer que tu naciste inválida y sin iniciativa.

jamás permitas que el dolor, la soledad, el resentimiento, las manipulaciones, los celos, la amargura y el rencor debiliten la enorme fuerza que el universo puso dentro de ti.

jamás te permitas perder tu dignidad ni dejar de ser quien deseas ser en manos de quien no te merece. ¡¡jamás se lo permitas a nadie!! ~ autor anónimo ~

#niunamas #vivasnosqueremos #niunamenos #metoo #felizañonuevo #noesno #solosiessi #cuentalo #mujeresempoderadas #powergirl #hermanayositecreo #yotecreo

text:
2018.

el año del máster: de ensayos de miles de palabras terminados a las 6 de la madrugada; de clases en las que he aprendido mucho más de lo que esperaba y otras que, bueno, como mínimo han sido surrealistas; de hacer centenares de calçots para gente de medio país y de medio mundo aunque no me gusten los calçots; de superarme a mí mismo; de acabar (por fin) el tfm y de saltar de alegría por el pasillo después de defenderlo.

el año de la política: de las tertulias en la radio; de subirme a la montaña rusa que es una campaña de municipales; de la moción de censura, el fin de la cita y la esperanza de un cambio frágil; de recordar que hay que decir “basta” y que crecer es aprender a tomar decisiones y vivir con las consecuencias; de cerrar etapas y tomar distancias; del #metoo y de reafirmarme que nosotros tenemos que estar pero que las protagonistas de esta lucha son ellas; del #mequeer, de pensar “no estamos tan mal pero, joder, lo que nos falta por conseguir” y de las infinitas salidas del armario.

el año de estar pluriempleado: de cuando llega el momento de tomar la decisión de dejar el trabajo en el que llevaba más de dos años (pero pocas veces había tenido algo tan claro); de empezar a trabajar en proyectos inspiradores porque hay gente que cree en mí; de acabar el año con dos trabajos y siendo mileurista a mis 26-casi-27 años.

text:
part 1 2018: a love story
.
this year was a long hard road. so much i had to let go of, so much i had to move on from, so much i had to embrace. it was overwhelming. i almost lost myself completely. .
the beginning of a slow death:
.
i realized early into my teacher training that i had a perfectionist monster living inside of me that was preventing me from being my most honest self. it's fangs were embeded in my soul, its claws had a stranglehold of my heart, its body coiled tight on my spirit. i chased this monster down, followed its trail and tracked it to it's lair. i had some questions, damn it! what i found, i was not ready for. i was not prepared for the flood of supressed bullshit that came pouring out. .
alcohol abuse, drug abuse, physical abuse, sexual abuse, food addiction, eating disorders, unresolved grief, resentment, body image issues, mass amounts of fear and shame, family curses, heartbreak, self loathing, chronic illness, denial, anger so much fucking anger;  you name it, i supressed, numbed and ran from it. i opened pandoras box and i was fucked. or so i thought. .
the messy middle:
.
for months i unpacked a lifetime of shit. i stayed away from social media; i dove into my practice (off the mat), i cancelled all diet and exercise plans, i read book after book after book; i lived a life of bunny slippers, constant bubble baths and rest; self care that had nothing to do with my looks but everything to do with my emotional/mental health. i allowed weight to pour on without giving 2 shits. i loved my daughter hard. i lost sleep, had panic attacks, binged, purged, numbed, i got back up. i looked in the mirror & felt sorry for that girl looking back at me, i didn't know her or recognize her and yet my heart ached for her. why had i done this? why had i let it get this bad? how had i gone so many years without ever acknowledging my pain? why? these were the questions i needed answered. this is what i sat with. i had some serious real healing ahead of me not superficial instagram inspiration bullshit but real gross dirty heart wrenching kill me now healing.
.
. **#tobecontinued** #cliffhanger
💄: @thevyletrose 📸: @goddessbylanzamanage

text:
cheers to 2019!! 2018 was a weird year for me. that said, it was a noteworthy year for several reasons i’ll list below:
.
🌟i got sliced through the front and backsides and became a #cyborg. i came back from that back surgery and am already squatting three plates for reps.
🌟i quit a job due to sexual harassment and found a better one. i never wrote about my #metoo story here because it’s still too raw, and it makes me super uncomfortable to even bring it up. but here i am, saying something.
🌟 i quit having imposter syndrome at work and started accepting responsibilities that i once would have thought were above me.
🌟 i moved to a new city that represents my vibe better 🤪. seriously, i think i just needed a change. when andrey and i get an idea in our heads, we move fast. i really like this about us.
🌟 i disconnected myself from a powerlifting meet calendar. this was the first year since 2013 i haven’t tried to be competitive in powerlifting. it was incredibly humbling to watch my would-be competitors out there while i sat on the sidelines injured. but it was humbling in a good way. i feel much more in charge of my time, and in control of what i do and where i go. adhering to a powerlifting calendar can be very restrictive in terms of enjoying life to its fullest.
🌟 i read more books for pleasure and personal development than i have any year thus far.
🌟 one more year with @beefpuffbarbell which has been one more year of building some beautiful coach-athlete relationships and developing athletes mentally and physically. we onboarded two new coaches and brought on a marketing coordinator, doubling our staff in size!
🌟 our family grew by two more fur babies, misha and ilya. and of course, we gained a cat instagram 😅. @chandreyscats
.
so, i guess it’s been a great year. thanks to all 10,000 of you who stuck around (and no thanks to the 10% or so of you who left 😅).
.
what are some of your big moments from 2018? what are you looking forward to in the new year?

text: ce n'est pas la photo où je suis la plus belle, mais c'est moi au naturel. c'est l'éducatrice en cpe, la fille qui fait du bénévolat, celle qui s'occupe des autres... la femme qui termine 2018 épuisée, mais heureuse de tous ses accomplissements. je suis indestructible. il m'a pris du temps pour le réaliser. mes blessures finissent par faire partie de ce que je suis. elles sont une part de ma personnalité et de ma révolte. mon côté féministe, acharnée; à la défense de toute forme de discrimination, me vient des épreuves que j'ai traversé. en 2019, soyez ouvert d'esprit, soyez vif et vivez avec vos valeurs au coeur. #metoo #moiaussi #strongwomen #force #féministe #convictions #valeurs #diversité #confiance #newyear #2018 #2019

text:
for 2017 i set out to put myself out there more... so:

1. i hopped on board with painting a mural (you can see it on the south wall of the @lawlerhousegallery in suisun, ca.) 2. painted the banner painting during a short #artistinresidency and “live”...in the store front window of the @fsvaa gallery at the solano town center in fairfield, ca. 
i was pretty proud of myself at the end of 2017.

so i raised the bar for 2018:

1. over new years i established a project using donated lipsticks called #metoo

2. i collaborated with the artist doug cooper, of suisun, ca.,to create an amazing ’living art’ piece that comes off the canvas and plays with light and shadows called paper boats

3. i put on a 2 week long solo show that included several of my social issue pieces, the show was called #hashtag and was held at the @coalshedstudios on mare island in vallejo, ca. it was an enormous success.

wow! right ‽ 
2018 blew me out of the water and brought more people in front of my art than i ever could have hoped for. 
onward.

what will 2019 bring?
how will i show up?
what will i do this coming year to up the bar?

text:
thank you everyone for an amazing 2018! this year, we created a new series of workshops, established new partnerships and continued to empower through music. we interviewed some amazing artists, shared a new line of merch and proudly witnessed the rise of alumni band @the.salmon.ella! we put aside our fears and fought for representation in music - on festival lineups and behind the scenes. when sexual assault in music hit the headlines, we stood up for survivors. and we were honoured to be named the @unitedwayottawa @gennextott gennext community builder of the year. 
we still have a lot of work to do to make music more inclusive and accessible, but with your help, we see progress! thank you for all of your support and see you in 2019! ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜💖
.
.
.

text:
il mio ultimo articolo per il 2018. 
il #2018 è stato l’anno globale in cui la determinazione delle ragazze e delle donne ha scosso gli assetti patriarcali. sono scese in piazza, hanno manifestato compatte. 
negli stati uniti è il #metoo che ha dato forza alle donne.

text:
new years eve reflection time.

there’s always something felt at the end of the year isn’t there?

whether it’s excitement at what next year might bring, relief that this years finally over, or bittersweet memories it seems to bring up definite emotions.

one thing i always do at the end of the year is look back at what the last 12 months have brought. 
what worked, what didn’t, what successes did i have. how have i grown? what have i contributed? who shared my journey with me?

this new year’s eve is no different but i have to confess feeling all of the above emotions. i’m hugely grateful for all the insights, lessons & understandings that have been gained, and to those who shared this journey with me, supporting, caring, sharing and just being there. it made a huge difference and you have my eternal thanks. relieved that this challenging, frustrating and painful year is about to be finally done. excited to see what opportunities the next 12 months have in store. and bittersweet at feeling the loss of my usual way of life for most of this year.

it’s been an interesting, bumpy year globally as well as personally. i’ve heard it called ‘the year of the woman’ as women emerge into positions of power and strength, the #metoo movement, the increased number of women moving into politics or running their own businesses. pretty wonderful hey? 
and not forgetting mother nature herself. she’s been busy too with volcanos, tsunamis, floods etc. 
it’s time we stand up and be the change. together.

wishing you all a great new years eve.

#understandings #challengingyear #wonderfulclients #lessonslearnt #reflection #newyearseve #yearofwomen #empowerment #bethechange #newopportunities #embracingchange #coaching #soulcoach #friendship

text:
happy new year, friends! i'm curious to hear any memories of the past year and resolutions for the next.

for me, i'm recalling my visit to this iconic 1600 baroque sculpture: the martyrdom of saint cecilia, by stefano maderno. outside this church i had a skirmish with an unfriendly tourist. i wrote a story, called conquerer, and it's about that tourist and my feelings on the # metoo movement. read it whenever you like on my website.

my resolution for 2019 is to show more kindness to strangers and loved ones every day. which is kind of a cop-out: i also want to build dat juicy booty. 🍑💦
have marvelous and safe(ish) celebrations tonight. 💜🎉
.
.
.

text:
black women were an invisible group whose existence and needs were ignored.”
even when broadly popular feminist causes are sparked by black women activists, they often don’t receive credit and their specific lens may fall out of focus as time goes on. take, for instance, the 2017 women’s march protesting the inauguration of president donald trump—co-founded by social justice activist tamika mallory and inspired by marches for civil rights in the 1990s—which received early criticism for seeming to co-opt those previous marches’ efforts and not including women of color in leadership from its earliest planning stages. more recently, the #metoo online movement to draw attention to pervasive sexual harassment was largely attributed to a tweet from actor alyssa milano, when the concept was actually put into play more than a decade ago by social activist tarana burke as part of her work building solidarity among young survivors of harassment and assault. “from enslavement to the women's suffrage movement to the civil rights movement to the current movement for the liberation of black life, black women are the engines of movement,” ike says. “we may not be seen under the hood, but no car moves without us.”
their activism, purchasing power, and social influence is all the more impressive considering the stiff hurdles black women still face. on average, black women earn only 67 cents to the white man’s dollar. while black women are now the most educated group in the u.s., as of 2016 they held just 8 percent of private sector jobs, with only 2 percent in leadership positions. perhaps that’s why black women’s median wealth is a stunning $200 compared to white women’s $15,640, and when considering black women with children as compared to their white counterparts, their wealth falls to $0, while white women’s still remains above $14,000. “we don't discuss how even with higher salaries than prior generations, phenomena like gentrification, glass ceilings, and increased cost of living limit our ability to be socially mobile,” says ike, noting that very little attention is paid to how much debt black women go into to finance their education and businesses. “collectively, we ar

text: a mourning commences. a new year stands upon the threshold, barren of what comes next. minutes arrive with grace to pummel forward, offering the future before most are ready. it arrives whether or not we turn from its existence, as the crown of tenacity rests upon the impermanence of a single moment. the echo of time's dying breath is a single leaf lost within a wintery landscape. listen as she grieves, see her eyes fill with what is no more, wait as she shifts to dust to transform.

text:
2018 has taught me many things:

1. i am stronger than i ever imagined. 🎆

2. i can love and feel love at volumes i didn't know existed. 🎆

3. i am capable of so much more than i give myself credit for sometimes. 🎆

4. the best gifts you could ever give new parents are time alone together and sleep. 🎆 
5. and lastly, 2018 showed me that humans are capable of great and terrible things. and i want my daughter to know what side of history i stand on. 🎆
.
.
.

text:
🌷all survivors respond, cope, and heal from their abuse in different ways, and paces.
.
🗣some speak their truth, some remain silent but seek therapy, some are still trying to figure out how to accept that they didn’t tell, and it wasn’t their fault..
.
🗣many may feel their abuse has taken over their lives, their is no success pass their abuse, they are what happened to them, and they are unworthy of love, and triumph..
..
🗣although having the courage to heal is daunting. taking back your life and power feels like an endless task, success seems incomprehensible, and failure feels like the norm. today is the day i’m here to show and tell you differently.
.
🗣yes, i speak my truth. i speak my truth to cope, i speak my truth to survive, i speak my truth to move forward, i speak my truth to break free, i speak my truth to develop self love and compassion, but most importantly i speak my truth so you will know can know you can heal too!.
..

text:
last up for our #yearinreview we leapt into development for #churchtoo. it was a new process for us in that we commissioned seven playwrights from across canada to write the piece working with @johnnywideman as a dramaturg. 
#churchtoo was our biggest tour to date, reaching over 2000 audience members and visiting communities in ontario, manitoba, and  saskatchewan. we also had our first show in toronto, independent from the festival circuits, at @assemblytheatre where we had two sold out shows!

we also worked with a brand new cast of actors. we were delighted to work with meghan fowler, robert murphy, lindsey middleton, brendan kinnon, and matt white from @greenlight_arts as our director. this is the first time we’d hired an entirely new creative team of actors and director, but it paid off to feature new voices, expanding and diversifying our team.

pictured: @greenlight_matt @lalalindseym @megatronf and robert murphy. 
#2018yearinreview #lookingback #development #theatre #actors #creation #tour #touringlife #team #cdncult #stagingchange #theatrebeat #metoo #timesup

text:
why your brain is your largest sex organ?
during sex there are 3 prominent neurochemicals that are involved and each has a significant affect on your brain.
dopamine: this chemical is present in men and women. it's the chemical that is responsible for the addictive nature of sex. it keeps you wanting that next fix. unfortunately, dopamine doesn't know the difference between positive and negative behaviors. so it rewards the brain for both. 
oxytocin: this chemical is found in the female and controls love and bonding. after sex, it increases her desire for touch and causes her to bond with the person she is in physical contact with. also causing her to bond with someone she only thought would be a casual hookup. 
vasopressin: this is the male version of the bonding chemical and is the cause of the man's connection with his partner. it is non-discriminatory and may result in an unintentional connection with a partner.
.
.

text:
elizabeth warren is running for president in 2020
#fashion #lifestyle #tech #trends
senator elizabeth warren has announced her exploratory committee to run for president in 2020, making her the first major candidate to enter the race. this committee will allow her to begin raising money for her campaign.the longtime harvard law professor turned massachusetts democratic senator announced a campaign focused on her desire to protect america’s middle class; she has long been public with her disapproval of big banks and unregulated capitalism. she has also been vocal about her support of the #metoo movement and women’s rights. in her video announcing her exploratory launch committee for the presidency, these are a few of her platforms.“in our country, if you work hard and play by the rules, you ought to be able to take care of yourself and the people you love. that’s a fundamental promise of america. a promise that should be true for everyone,” she says. “i’ve spent my career getting to the bottom of why america’s promise works for some families, but others, who work just as hard, slip through the cracks into disaster.”warren is already familiar with the barbarous commentary of president, donald trump who has referred to her as “pocahontas” and a “fraud” on multiple occasions. he has already announced his bid for re-election. according to the new york times, warren’s fellow party members questioned if making her dna results public was playing right into his hands. the cherokee nation called her efforts to prove her heritage "inappropriate and wrong."the 2020 presidential race is expected to be a crowded one. there are the anticipated candidates we already know such as former vice president joe biden and senator bernie sanders. many prospective candidates – more than three dozen considering democratic bids coming from business leaders, senators, governors, and mayors – have not previously sought a role in the white…

#fashion #lifestyle #tech #trends
senator elizabeth warren has announced her exploratory committee to run for president in 2020, making her the first major candidate to enter the race. this committee will allow her to begin raising money for her campaign.the longtime harvard law professor turned massachusetts democratic senator announced a campaign focused on her desire to protect america’s middle class; she has long been public with her disapproval of big banks and unregulated capitalism. she has also been vocal about her support of the #metoo movement and women’s rights. in her video announcing her exploratory launch committee for the presidency, these are a few of her platforms.“in our country, if you work hard and play by the rules, you ought to be able to take care of yourself and the people you love. that’s a fundamental promise of america. a promise that should be true for everyone,” she says. “i’ve spent my career getting to the bottom of why america’s promise works for some families, but others, who work just as hard, slip through the cracks into disaster.”warren is already familiar with the barbarous commentary of president, donald trump who has referred to her as “pocahontas” and a “fraud” on multiple occasions. he has already announced his bid for re-election. according to the new york times, warren’s fellow party members questioned if making her dna results public was playing right into his hands. the cherokee nation called her efforts to prove her heritage "inappropriate and wrong."the 2020 presidential race is expected to be a crowded one. there are the anticipated candidates we already know such as former vice president joe biden and senator bernie sanders. many prospective candidates – more than three dozen considering democratic bids coming from business leaders, senators, governors, and mayors – have not previously sought a role in the white…

text:
california’s #metoo law is about to go into effect. here’s what it does.
#fashion #lifestyle #tech #trends
california is one of the states leading the way to lasting change by restricting the use of non-disclosure agreements. the new law will go into effect on january 1, 2019. the law, signed by outgoing governor jerry brown in september, forbids the use of an nda in settlements involving harassment, sexual assault, or discrimination based on sex, the los angeles times reports.dozens of men and the wrongdoings they have fought to conceal have been uncovered in the wake of the #metoo movement and a single document has become one of the most prevalent mechanisms: the non-disclosure agreement. ndas were exposed this year for the long role they have played in silencing victims and enabling men to commit serial misconduct and avoid repercussion s. the document has been extended far past its roots as a tool to prevent employees from sharing trade secrets and become something frequently used by lawyers and companies in settlement of sexual harassment and misconduct claims to keep them out of the public eye.last spring, new york endorsed a new nda law that also starts tomorrow and only permits confidentiality clauses at the request of the victim. the british parliament is also in discussions to pass legislation in response to the #metoo movement.according to usa today, all 50 states have passed bills in the last two years surrounding sexual harassment, rape kits, and non-disclosure agreements. another law enacted in california is giving publicly held companies until the end of 2019 to have at least one woman on their board of directors.some experts believe that these laws should go further, suggesting that a law be put in place that prevents perpetrators from leaving companies with substantial financial compensation. many men accused of misconduct have left their respective employers with payouts amounting to tens and even hundreds of millions…
link: https://ivendr.com/2018/12/31/californias-metoo-law-is-about-to-go-into-effect-heres-what-it-does/

text:
your spending in your state: money diaries from all 50 states
#fashion #lifestyle #tech #trends
it's been a big year for money diaries! from publishing a diary every day (except for major holidays), to the money diaries book by lindsey stanberry, it's safe the say that our beloved series about spending and saving reached new heights in 2018.for the money diary fans who have been paying attention, we've been running an ongoing series all year called your spending in your state. we set an ambitious goal for ourselves at the beginning of the year to publish at least one diary from every state to capture the spending habits and daily rituals of women from across the country.on the last day of 2018, we're celebrating the fact that we did it! from hawaii to maine, we've published one diary from each of the 50 states. so if you're looking for a great money diary binge to close out the year, you can find all the entries from your spending in your state.we also followed up with our favorite ops (and yours) of 2018, so be sure to check out what they've been up to — and what they learned — from writing a money diary. and let us know in the comments if you want to see your spending in your state or another special series in 2019!like what you see? how about some more r29 goodness, right here?california's #metoo law is about to go into effect. here's what it does.a week in brooklyn, ny, on a $32,000 incomethe 2019 money moves to make for your zodiac sign

text:
#bali 2018 in review! you all sowed into me as i started this journey to write my #memoir unprotected. i first want to thank each of you who contributed to my go fund me! secondly my bff from high school @actressveronicaslater for making my travel across the globe possible! 
now you all sent me to #bali so why am i still ✍🏿 writing... 🧐🤔and what did you do in bali.... :
:

1) first and foremost bali was the medicine i needed to keep me moving through this journey. :
:

2) writing about #trauma is traumatic for real for real. my journey in bali helped me to practice mindfulness in a way that eased the pain of reliving my life... .
:
:

3) while in bali god made clear to me that she is everywhere and in everything. i’ve paid more attention to nature than i ever have since bali which created many more mindful moments that i have ever had—-for example-a mindful walk  often replaced the images of being raped from my head that i had written on paper so i could go to the next part of the story. rather than shutdown
:
:

4) in bali i made friends from australia @tessastowe from india @jayahiranandani @poornimajyoti 
and from bail @vebutar 
@dikadeparko @soedhei and many more...
:
5) in bali i figured out how i wanted to proceed with tackling the edit of my original manuscript-which might i add the new work looks nothing like the old... 😛i done that thang and bali gave me the push
:
:

i will be forever grateful to everyone who was apart of my #bali experience. our intra- connectedness has guided me through this last year. your desire for me to succeed helped to provide an environment to succeed...........
:
:
finally!! no date to announce yet but i do know it. 🙈keep praying 🙏🏼keep cheering- 👏🏼keep sending your positive energy my way as i complete my memoir—- namaste *sips tea* ☕️💋 —————————————————————
#blackgirlsrock #womenempowerment #womenwhosupportwomen #author #essencemagazine #womanism #authorsofinstagram #hivaidsawareness #womanist #feminist #metoo

text:
well 2018 is coming to a close. i’m not going to say this year has been the best of my life of the worst of my life, because in all honesty, its been neither. i’ve had many ups and downs as always but i have certainly learnt a lot about myself (and also a lot about biochemistry ty for that university🤓)
as i said in one my previous posts, i want to focus on worrying less and living in the moment in 2019 but i also want to continue doing exactly what i am doing and working on improving my physical and mental health. i want to thank all of you amazing people for supporting me this year❤️
may next year bring everyone lots of happiness (and lots of tasty food and relaxation too ofc😏)

text:
goodbye 2018 🌙 it's been a year full of lots of amazing things that i'm so grateful for: starting stand-up comedy, taking my play to the edfringe, a cracking year at lipa and some real gifts of characters as well as lots of laughter and time spent with people who mean the world to me. it's also been full of challenges, lots of lows, and so many moments where i've really appreciated the amazing friends i've got for their support and love ✨ here's to 2019 with a big thank u, next 🎉 
and a lot of love to anyone who finds this time of year difficult for whatever reason ❤️ our country is struggling right now: there's a mental health crisis with funding being cut everywhere, a huge rise in homelessness, awful stigma against refugees, and fear and hate in many places (i could go on). the arts have been threatened again by funding cuts and the inequality within our industry has been highlighted by #metoo and #timesup and over seas with trump and kavanaugh. now more than ever we need to be united, so please be kind always, because this government may not be and we need to stand together and look after each other. ❤️❤️❤️ #lakedistrict #newyear #goodbye2018 #thankunext #hello2019

text:
to the #sisters who have found themselves, alone and in the arms of another. to the sons who have achieved and dreamed and become and surprised. to the brothers who have cried alongside #metoo. to the partners who have carried us when the cold and the trail and the exhaustion has been too great to traverse alone. to the mothers and fathers who have found supernatural strength, perseverance, healing and #hope. to the #daughters! to the daughters! to us all, through the dark disaster of the hardest of years, as we rise. see, this. here. it is in the great challenge that we greatly overcome. see, this. here. we are living, still.

to my newest brother, the lover of my dearest sister, who said "fuck it" to what was and embraced what could be. to my sister(s) who realized that they could carry another and nurture and to those who said, "no more," to being underappreciated and less than. to us all, every one, becoming. #becoming.

first the fall. then the rise.

here's to 2019 and the tracks we've laid towards progress, despite obstacles. we are the ones who move forward and onward. we sing songs and raise banners and hold hands. we cry. sometimes everyone cries. and we boldy claim a future that we believe in. for self. for children. for all. (but #2019 is for first tracks into that future, lighting flares and leading the way. here's where we stop talking and start doing.) onward. upward. let's rise. (thank you #2018 for grit and resilience and the fire that burns in the pit of your stomach when you lose it all and don't know the way but really nothing else. don't let the door hit ya....)

text:
another beautiful year that went by. with almost 5 beautiful countries explored. not too bad for an adventurer like me. this year has been the most peaceful year considering how much i remained patient and controlled my anger and it is all because i spent a lot of time focusing on myself on what i need to do and prioritizing my needs.

i made some meaningful connections this year and it is incredible how happy some people can make being miles away and always keep you motivated and tell you to believe in yourself.

some left the city which made me feel sad, and i left some for my own good. and not to forget and remember family is not important but it is everything…

as a country we have had couple of major disasters like kerala & coorg floods, amritsar train disaster and the kolkata bridge collapse. i hope we support each other in such situations rather than blaming and coming up with some weird religious theories and help re-build the nation to make a better living place.

let’s not forget to spread smiles to those in need. let’s also not forget to respect women & children and stop harassing and make india a safest country for them. with #metoo movement evolving lot of women addressed their issues on the abuse and the count of such incidents have been massive.

some of the greatest things that happened this year is when india got its first ever all female swat team. and of course, when supreme court made lgbt rights legal. over all let’s not forget the people at borders who keep us safe every day.

on that note, i wish your tomorrow is more prosperous, happy and successful than yesterday and today. wish you a very happy new year 2019.

with love,

swetha kumar

text:
cheers!
 2018 was packed with a lot, and i wanted to encourage everyone to unpack their year. 💎
 my year started off with me selling my car before i enlisted in the navy, due to dead transmission. i became a united states sailor, something i've wanted for 6 years, because i thought it was the only way i was ever going to save anyone else. this dream was ripped away from me, it did not matter that i had a high score on the asvab, or that i knew everything a sailor should know. in a world where 1 in 2 women suffer violence, the navy is not lady-friendly in requiring waivers for every incidence of trauma.... (women get booted for having been raped/abused/assaulted/etc. due to risk of ptsd. in case you didn't know lives got ruined outside of the trauma itself.) i came home to a bank account emptied, a living nightmare, and heavy suicidal feelings.
 i was overweight some, and i had nothing left in me. i tried being tough. i bought another car with borrowed money, but it broke down 2 months later, needing many repairs. i traded it in for my edge, which totaled itself 2 months later also, draining every penny i had earned in that short time. i then lost my job for requesting a raise.  i lost all faith in love, marriage, soulmates, life purpose, being respected and happy, all of it. my art was lost.  i was scared to get close to people, and still am not comfortable with it. however, the healing i have experienced has been monumental! ❤️ i was able to get into yet another car, i have been preparing my business consulting agency that will specialize in sm advertising, i have been chipping away at my art and ensuring i maintain some sort of flow, i got my body back and made it mine, found love in a hopeless place, and i made sure to have more down time with my beautiful babies. i have learned the meaning and the value of self-care.
 everyone has sat with me through all the bad in 2018. now, we could get to rise up together for 2019, and there are plenty of projects to be had!
*all projects will be announced in my next post!* 💎
 thank you, much love and light, hang in strong. this path to healing and happiness has been a wild one, but so worth the wait and effort! ❤️

text:
did you know that the @merriamwebster 2018 “#wordoftheyear” is justice?

in light of the #metoo movement, justice has been on the minds of many survivors and their allies.

at #vibs, we work tirelessly to achieve justice in all its definitions for victims of domestic violence, rape and sexual assault, human trafficking, and elder abuse. we possess a caring and knowledgeable staff of over forty individuals who provide hotline intervention, counseling, advocacy, court accompaniment, outreach, and community education.

since 1976, vibs has reached thousands of people. in 2019, we would like the opportunity to help thousands more. with your generous end-of-year donation, we can work together to restore justice to those who need it most.

please click the #linkinourbio for more information on how we can create futures free of violence. 🕊️

text:
ahhh....the peace, tranquility, and comfort of being with someone you love and trust. ⚘ ⚘

the gift of intimacy and authenticity comes with accepting each other faults, misgivings, mistakes, weaknesses, and wrong-doings. ⚘ ⚘

without such there is no relationship that will stand the test of time. ⚘ ⚘
it’s all or nothing.  when we withhold any part of ourselves from the one(s) we love, we forfeit the magic of that connection we all seek in life. ⚘ ⚘

i’m learning the hard work of looking in the mirror and being honest with myself.  i see someone who used to be scared of what he saw for many years. i’ve hidden behind coping mechanisms i created to keep me safe from not trusting those around me.  everything became second nature to keep others out because i felt worthless and dirty inside. ⚘ ⚘

a tragic side-effect of child sexual abuse. ⚘ ⚘

if you’re a survivor of any kind of abuse or trauma, remember to take many good, long looks in the mirror and do the hard work to #findyourself before you try and #giveyourself to someone else. ⚘ ⚘

the gift of intimacy and trust will be worth it. ⚘ ⚘ ....so i’ve heard.  here’s to 2019 and more hard work! ⚘ ⚘ 🤜🤛 💪🏾 🏋️‍♂️
#metoowhatnow #mentalhealthawareness #depression #overcomingdepression #cptsd #ptsd #suicideawareness #loveyourself #speakyourstory #metoo #metoomvmt

text:
wow so many things happened in 2018 that this year honestly felt like it was 10 (& apparently these are your faves? #bestnine2018 ??) i graduated my ma program at sdsu, wrote & finished my thesis, and was accepted into my phd program at the u of a, i wrote some cool shit and made beautiful art with friends, i figured out how to perform queer/trans professionalism and was able to attend multiple conferences, and i worked on my relationship with my #bodymindspirit. 
what didn't make instagram's algorithm cut ➡️ i cultivated an amazing queer family, i launched @queerfutures_ with @queerporvenir , i moved to az with @stafit_syd , @shealynschlauderaff and @bre_skiski got married, i got a few gay awards, i started seeing doctors to take care of my physical health, and i ended the year surrounded by my amazing family. and obviously these 10 pictures cant capture it all either. 
2018 was definitely in my top 5 bad years of my life, but i would also say it was truly the best and most rewarding yet. i was able to work on putting myself first and also on not feeling guilty for removing harmful people from my life. and that work showed in what i was able to accomplish, who i was able to help and the work i was able to create. 
and all of this has shown how far i have come in building a support system but also in building strength in myself to work through horrible life events without losing myself completely. this was a year of kindness, tenderness, achievement & pain. healing is never done, accountability is never done, self-work/inner work is never done. but even as these are always in progress, it doesn't stop us from being able to help and guide others through support, love & kindness ✨❤
.
.
.
.
.
#growth #2018reflections #queerfutures #bodymindspirit #health #academia #phd #writer #poetry #disability #queer #chronicpain #queerfamily #chosenfamily #victimsurvivor #metoo #seeyousoon2019

text: 2018 has been a great year but with this post i want to do things a bit differently and share with you some lessons that i learnt from a bad experience. so here goes: towards the end of this year i was sexually assaulted by my boss at work. a family man, 25 years older than me. not just once, three times. not just by words, but physically. the severity of sexual assault is broad so i want to start with saying that in my case it was not extreme (he grabbed me and forced himself on me a number of times, all whilst in the office). nevertheless the impact, mentally, was still destructive which is why i feel sharing this is important in case it can help anyone else. the most important lesson of all: you have a voice and you are not alone. in my case, i did not realise this at first; i was scared, and i kept silent for almost a month. i looked up to this person. i trusted him. i let him guide me in my career. eventually, i couldn’t take it anymore but instead of reporting him, i thought it best to confront him. all i wanted was an apology and reassurance this would never happen again. to my surprise he turned it on me, blamed me for the situation, never apologised and tried to play it off as ‘having a laugh’. at this point, it was his word against mine and i had no evidence…or so he thought. i am lucky enough to have a great other half in my life who eventually made me realise i’m not on my own. he convinced me that when going into this meeting i should record the conversation with my phone. the next day i reported my boss, and with this evidence i never saw him again. my other half also encouraged me to speak about what happened, with friends and family. when i did, i realised opening up made me feel not so alone and that people were willing to listen. on reflection, why did feel like i was alone? i am quite an emotional person, and growing up i suppose i didn’t really have that guidance on how to manage my emotions which is why i turned to yoga. yoga has helped me overcome a lot, and even though i know i have a long way to go, i know i am on the right path… please see my comment below for the end to this story.

text:
as i reflect back, 2018 was a year of extreme highs and lows. 
love ❤️ and heartbreak 💔. doing yet another elimination diet in my quest to figure out my food needs 🍞(my grieving of gluten), finding the sport that changed my body, heart and soul 🥊 and getting so stressed from work and school multiple times i considered going on leave 🤯. living with dear friends 👩‍👩‍👧 and then navigating living alone 🤷🏻‍♀️. ending friendships both by my choice or the others’ and the grief that goes along with that 🌱 the joy of reconnecting with a friend who shaped me 🌻 the adventures of making new friends 🌺 and the blessing of deepening and continuing friendships. saying goodbye to my closest friend and colleague moving 😢 and waiting in anticipation for the next chapter 📚. figuring out that i’m an enneagram #4️⃣ and now doing the emotional work 🌞. filing yet another sexual harassment report and was both heartbroken and empowered by the #metoo movement and stories 💕. traveling and new adventures ✈️ and feeling deep loneliness despite the constant movement. learning how to incorporate a not-for-profit, move go into that new journey, file for charitable status, form a board of directors, and facilitate another amazing summer of go in young peoples lives 🌈, while some days being so tired and stressed i’d give myself migraines, nausea, and stomach pain 🤕. .
although 2018 had its challenges for me, i know it was a worse year for many. because of where i live, the colour of my skin, my health and ability, i got to turn the news off when it was too hard to watch. i commit to be a better ally. for those who lost loved ones, jobs, struggled with illness and for whom cant wait for 2018 to be over, i’m sending you prayers and love for a new year. .

my dreams for 2018:
-to love deeply
-travel to one place i havent been
-become a better ancestor and ally (join me in the #meandwhitesupremacy challenge)
-show my friends how grateful i am for their love and support in my life
-continue going to therapy, the gym, and enneagram workshops -choosing happiness more
-reading for pleasure -treating every day at work as a challenge and privilege

love ❤️ and heabreak 💔. doing yet another elimination diet in my quest to figure out my food needs 🍞(my grieving of gluten), finding the spo that changed my body, hea and soul 🥊 and getting so stressed from work and school multiple times i considered going on leave 🤯. living with dear friends 👩‍👩‍👧 and then navigating living alone 🤷🏻‍♀️. ending friendships both by my choice or the others’ and the grief that goes along with that 🌱 the joy of reconnecting with a friend who shaped me 🌻 the adventures of making new friends 🌺 and the blessing of deepening and continuing friendships. saying goodbye to my closest friend and colleague moving 😢 and waiting in anticipation for the next chapter 📚. figuring out that i’m an enneagram  and now doing the emotional work 🌞. filing yet another sexual harassment repo and was both heabroken and empowered by the  movement and stories 💕. traveling and new adventures ✈️ and feeling deep loneliness despite the constant movement. learning how to incorporate a not-for-profit, move go into that new journey, file for charitable status, form a board of directors, and facilitate another amazing summer of go in young peoples lives 🌈, while some days being so tired and stressed i’d give myself migraines, nausea, and stomach pain 🤕. .
although 2018 had its challenges for me, i know it was a worse year for many. because of where i live, the colour of my skin, my health and ability, i got to turn the news off when it was too hard to watch. i commit to be a better ally. for those who lost loved ones, jobs, struggled with illness and for whom can not wait for 2018 to be over, i’m sending you prayers and love for a new year. .

my dreams for 2018:
-to love deeply
-travel to one place i havent been
-become a better ancestor and ally (join me in the  challenge)
-show my friends how grateful i am for their love and suppo in my life
-continue going to therapy, the gym, and enneagram workshops -choosing happiness more
-reading for pleasure -treating every day at work as a challenge and privilege

text:
good-bye 2018. you've been so good to me. i look forward to a very colorful 2019.

here's a sampling of my 2018 #soulpotraits for #healingptsd and staying #calminthechaos of life and #listeningtohigherself. some deal with #lossoflovedone, #grief,  #politicalinjustice, #abortionrights, #blacklivesmatter, #metoo and #sexualharrasment as well as #womeninbusiness conflicts with other women. 
i'm ready to plunge into taking my work into new levels. new places and new ways. color!!! wow, what an image: diving to take flight.

my first goals for 2019 (first week!!!) are to complete the www.calminthechaosbook.com site and a tiny-but-mighty thing (in my head) standing in the way of publishing it. "some part of you always knows what you need. i help you connect with that knowing through a message from your soul" #higherself. 
you can get your own personal soul portrait about the issue that keeps you up at night. dm me if you just can't wait for me to get my site updated!! is it personal? family? work? 
you know this - even your business or your project has its own soul.  i can help you or group come to resolution over a conflict through a soul portrait process. yes, your family too. 
a really big goal and project for 2019 is implementing a soul portrait process for mothering/fathering:  its creating the #parentingmanual they say we don't have. i'm bringing together my decades of education and practice in primal #attachmenttherapy and lifetime of art, to do a personal book for baby. 
this can be for a new mother-baby dyad and father, processing the baby's experience with their #doula or #midwife or it can be an adult who wishes to heal their disconnect and be in alignment with self. 
intrigued? i hope so.  stay tuned!! #conceptionhealing #birthtrauma 
here's to bringing it all together in 2019!!!

text:
i was on a public bus one time, on the way home from pu college. the journey usually took about 30-40 minutes, and i was lucky enough to find myself a seat by the window. a middle-aged lady planted herself next to me. i soon fell asleep. at some point during the journey, i remember waking up and groggily noticing that the middle-aged lady was gone, and someone else was seated in her stead. considering i was in the front of the bus, the 'ladies only' section, i assumed that it was another female passenger. 
without fully looking up, i realised that my stop was still a while away. so i dropped my head down back to my sleeping position. this was when i felt a thumb slowly and discreetly feeling up my breast. i was in shock at first, but rage took over pretty quickly. i pushed the man's hand away and stood up; i shouted at him loudly accusing him of indecency. 
the crowded bus fell silent, and my own voice rang in my ears.  why were you touching me? why are you sitting in the 'ladies only' zone when so many women are hanging on to the bars? don't you feel ashamed of yourself? all the while i asked this twenty-something-year-old man these questions, he looked sheepishly ahead making no eye contact with me. the bus conductor then made his way through the crowd and ordered the man to alight from the bus. 
this should have brought me some relief - the threat had been thrown out, literally - but it didn't. i felt a deep sense of despair. what made me really sad that day were not the man's indecent actions, but the silent, implicative looks of my fellow passengers. as though i was the one who had incited the man, as though i was kicking up a fuss for nothing, as though i was not strong enough to deal with the atrocities of the world. .

under section 354a of the indian penal code 1860 making unwelcomed physical advances involving sexual overtures, including sexually coloured remarks, is punishable with rigorous imprisonment which could be extended upto three years, or with fine, or both.

@timesupnow @unwomen @metoomvmt @womenintheworld 
#metoo #standagainstharassment #reclaimthestreets #fightsexualharassment #endviolenceagainstwomen #timesup #unwomen #unwomenindia

text:
chief editor @vivivigliar picked 10 articles from 2018 for you to read. in 2019, we vow to raise more awareness, raise our voices higher and bring our community together through what unites us.

1. ‘how to be a feminist dad?’ gender expert sebastián molano shares his insight on being a father in the age of #metoo
2. ‘time to hold governments accountable for destroying the planet’s rainforests’ - esben marcussen from @greenpeace says we must abandon the idea that the world’s rainforests can be saved by technocrats, it is a political undertaking.
3. ‘is facebook threatening your ability to protest?’ - facebook claims that it’s mission is to “bring the world together”, but at what price?
4. ‘latin american feminism: what now?’ explores how the green tide feminist movement in argentina has grown and expanded, and how its future looks like
5. ‘to stop the institutionalisation of children, stop volunteering in orphanages’ explains how well-intentioned foreigners perpetuate the exploitation of children. (a faveourite of @jkworling)
6. ‘we could end the plastic nightmare, here’s how’ tells how circular plastic economics could be a solution to the #plastic problem
7. ‘single, childless, career driven: problematic’ from out #caribbeanconnections column explains how two women ascended to positions of power and were questioned about their private life
8. ‘rwanda genocide: lest we forget’ is a homage to the victims of the rwandan genocide and a reflection on the importance of memory.
9. ‘lgbt resistance under bolsonaro’  analyses the impact of the bolsonaro election in brazil on the lgbt+ community in brazil
10. ‘bits of borno’ looks at the incredible work of @bitsofborno , the photographer who is showing the world a different side of war-torn #nigerian borno state.
.
.
.
#newyear #nye #goodreads #writersofinstagram #bestpicks #human #humanrights #climatechange #lgbt #caribbean #rwanda #deforestation #feminism #parenthood #facebook #argentina #greentide #abortolegalya #newyearseve

text:
🎉gott nytt år🎉

2018 har varit ett fullspäckat år för oss i män uppsala. vi är otroligt tacksamma för alla fina möten och fantastiska människor som vi har fått chansen att träffa under året. vi vill också passa på att rikta ett extra stort tack till våra medlemmar och du som kommit till våra träffar, möten, deltagit i samtalsgrupper eller som på något sätt stöttat vårt arbete mot en mer jämställd värld fri från våld. tack ❤️
⏺️⏺️⏺️
nu blickar vi framåt, under 2019 vill vi kunna engagera fler och möjliggöra för fler att i olika former delta och medverka i vårt arbete. startskottet för #metoo-rörelsen som på allvar sparkade igång den här rörelsen har satt sitt ljus på alla mäns ansvar. även om det nu gått över ett år ser vi att det finns mycket jobb att göra. det ska också kommas ihåg att det här inte är en ny fråga, kvinnojourer och feministiska rörelser runt om i sverige har arbetat med de här frågorna under årtionden. tillsammans kan vi sätta ett stopp för det sexuella våldet och skapa ett tryggare samhälle för alla, fritt från begränsande normer kopplat till kön och hur man förväntas vara. 2019 fortsätter det här arbetet. hoppas du vill vara med oss, hör gärna av dig till oss på uppsala@mfj.se om du vill veta mer, som en fin start på det nya året kan du också bli medlem och stötta vårt arbete lokalt via mfj.se/medlem. gott nytt! 💚🎉

text:
2018 has been a heck of a year for feminism. the number of feminists and socially vocal feminists has grown drastically. due to this, we have accomplished many things. we started the #metoo movement as well as #whyistay. voters in ireland struck down one of the most draconian abortion bans in the developed world. women in saudi arabia are finally able to drive legally, and female candidates broke historic ground in the us midterm elections. 2018 was probably one of the first years we started to focus on things males face. although nothing too prominent has begun, we have started the journey to help bring males that are abused or assaulted out of the shadows, and by extension their attackers. 
now, i understand that sounds all rainbows and daisies, but there is still a lot to accomplish. first and foremost, we must continue our current efforts. we have not yet reached the point in which we can stop. many girls still do not get enough food or respect, let alone an education. in 2019, i would like to bring more light to what males face as well. even they endure stigma, body shame and assault. of course not all men, but it still needs to be talked about. 
as can be seen in my bio, i am more than a feminist. in 2019, i would like to focus on suicide and depression as well. these days, depression has become part of ‘pop culture’ and phrases like ‘i want to kill myself” are thrown around lightly. we often forget that some people actually mean that.

2019 is a new year, full of opportunities. we must seize these to bring equality to everyone. if you’re reading this, chances are you are privileged. and no i don't mean spoiled, rachel green privileged. you have a roof over your head, an education, food and water. you need to understand that there are many not privileged as us. let’s make 2019 a little easier for them. there are many charities you can donate too that can be easily found on the internet. 2019 will be an amazing year for us regardless - what with our wifi and devices -, let’s make it amazing for everyone too. here’s to a new year full of advancements, progress and equality 🥳

text:
this year we lost both of our beloved pets and the world lost stan lee, aretha franklin, winnie mandela, and stephen hawking. also one of link’s sweet little friends from school passed away this year and he experienced his first funeral. this has not been our favorite year to say the least. 
that being said, there have been things to celebrate in 2018. my oldest child started kindergarten and is thriving in school, i finished my reading list for the year, my brother and sister in law are expecting their first baby, i got to see a lot of new shows with my favorite guy @joshbuwalda, so many more progressives were elected to congress, the #metoo movement happened, saudi arabia lifted it’s driving ban for women, voter turn outs in 2018 midterms were the highest in a century, and as of ten minutes ago my husband hit his sales goal for the year 🎉🙌
here’s to hoping that 2019 brings more good than bad. 
#happynewyear #goodbye2018

that being said, there have been things to celebrate in 2018. my oldest child staed kindergaen and is thriving in school, i finished my reading list for the year, my brother and sister in law are expecting their first baby, i got to see a lot of new shows with my favorite guy  so many more progressives were elected to congress, the  movement happened, saudi arabia lifted it’s driving ban for women, voter turn outs in 2018 midterms were the highest in a century, and as of ten minutes ago my husband hit his sales goal for the year 🎉🙌
here’s to hoping that 2019 brings more good than bad.

text:
as we head into a new year we wanted to share our #lastread of 2018 with you. we'd also love to hear what your last read was, so feel free to share 👇🏻👇🏼👇🏽👇🏽👇👇🏾👇🏿
_____________________ 
women and power is a feminist manifesto to add to your bookshelf in 2019, if it isn't already there. written by scholar and classicist mary beard, originally as 2 separate lectures in 2014 and 2017, this short work tackles the subject of female silence and female power (in western culture) by referring back to greek and roman antiquity. the author successfully avoids falling into the trap of labeling things as merely misogynistic; her point is to understand and explain the misogynistic structures in place before we can even think about restructuring them.
_____________________ 
how is it that public speaking and debate is a predominantly male territory? perhaps homer has an answer for us: in his highly revered poem odyssey, the son telemachus explicitly tells his mother penelope to “shut up” and go back upstairs. in the era of trump and #metoo, depressingly not much appears to have changed; men continue to threaten or shame or silence women who speak up and speak out in order to feel like they're in control. 
_____________________ 
continually using pejorative language for women who speak out ("whine" for example) only results in undermining or erasing the authority of what we have to say. so that even when we do speak, we risk not being heard or taken seriously - just like the woman in the punch cartoon that mary beard mentions (“that’s an excellent suggestion, miss triggs. perhaps one of the men here would like to make it”).
_____________________ 
it is not on women to adopt male mannerisms, such as a deeper voice, in order to be taken seriously. as a society, we have a responsibility to rethink all structures that work to shut certain people out. onwards and upwards in 2019 eh?! #feministessays #feministbookclub #feministbookshelf #womenandpower #whatimreading #marybeard #bookflatlay #bookworm #bibliophile

text:
2018, you were pretty freaking good and freeing!

spent a year home with my favorite little man and watched him grow 💙.
.

worked on my health and concentrated on bettering myself physically and mentally.

found the strength inside to come forward about something that happened 12 years ago despite how terrifying it was. thru that, i have found an indescribable freedom!

made new friends and learned who my real friends were. not in a negative way! only positive ❤️ rekindled some old friendships that are now family again!

now ending this year happier than ever surrounded by those i love most. 2018, you made me stronger. so much stronger than i ever thought i could be.

2019, i’m so ready for you. i have a feeling you’re going to be even more amazing.

text:
oh, i have a friend. i'm really grateful for people who use the internet properly and bypass all the free porn for *information*. jstore is one click away from pornhub; if you upgrade your phone you can do both at once
.

the advent of the internet is one long social thought experiment: now that the world fits inside our palm how to use it? free porn
.

it's not a judgement, but it has been proven true that most people just use personal experience to flush out their understanding of the world, and while that works great for sex, it doesn't apply universally. you have to read. about the world
.

its interesting that the white mediocre, the one who was cussed out by my friend, spoke with so much authority on race but doesn't even know the base parameters of racism. now, theres always room to intellectually grow, i'm in school so i get it. life is tricky when reduced to an onslaught of theory, all which bounce off each other. but um, we've been stuck in the same race discussion bc experiential emotionality (hurt feelings) is often the starting point that ends in certain "political violence"
.

nobody gives a fuck about your hurt feelings, except for the fist in your orbital bone
.

the #metoo movement? cathartic but entirely ineffective; it had nothing real to grasp intellectually. sex is bad? harrasment is anything that hurts your feelings? it all leads to rape? there was nothing more than a bunch of far-too-simple hashtags, all which said nothing about the larger context: sex as american trade, and the booming economy that is actually responsible for silencing "your" voice
.

we saw not one dollar extracted from americas participation in the global sex trade, largely bc messages, as wide as they might have seemed, were bound by *class*. the majority audience for sex as labor is young black girls, globally. but within that we see pennies traded on behalf of age, skin tone, *venerability*... and if you cross back through the "middle passage" we see religion play a signature role in sex slavery from nigeria to benin
.

these are the details of economic development that have everything to do with the maintenance of a rather tricky and crude global conciousness
.

text:
señora de belen, señora de una noche siempre esperada.
señora de la paz, la alegría, la esperanza.
señora de los pobres y de los niños.
señora de los que no tienen nada, de los que sufren soledad.
señora de los que peregrinan, como tú, sin hallar porque no encuentran comprensión en ningún alma, tampoco una posada.
enséñanos a ser pobres y pequeños. a no tener ambición por nada.
a desprendernos y entregarnos. a ser los mensajeros de la paz y la esperanza.
que esta noche de luz que tú nos diste sea el comienzo de una claridad que no se acaba.
que el amor sustituya a la violencia.
que haya justicia entre los hombres y los pueblos.
que en la verdad, la justicia y el amor, se haga la verdadera paz.  que así sea.  con esta oración a nuestra señora de belen.
les deseo un muy feliz 2019 🍀🍀🍀. #yocreo #justiciapordebora #metoo #noalmaltratoanimal⛔️❌debodecir  #miracomonosponemos

text:
it was my first job, i was so happy and nervous... and naive (i was 24yo). i started working in an office where probably 70% where man. 
i never consider myself an attractive woman until that day, i got too much attention, more that i would probably ever wanted. 
the associate partner got interested in me, he was 36 and he had a girlfriend. 
i was insecure on what to do, i said no for so long and he kept insisting so i finally agreed to go out with him, he said “i can’t believe no one is fucking you” sadly i found it kind of funny at that time. 
i went out with him but never felt safe to have sex with him, he scared me somehow, so one day he invited me to a party, got me drugged, beaten me and raped me. 
i was so confused, i barely had flash backs and he almost broke my back. he told me the other day that i insisted for him to fuck me, that i begged for it. 
all everyone could see is that i was drunk and i was the affair.

text:
thanks for all you have brought #2018 
for some it was wonderful, for some it was hard- for most it was a bit of both ...to predict what will happen in the #newyear is like seeing a gust of wind coming your way....you’ll only realise its there when it hits you . #2019 can only be greater than what we have walked through so far- #metoo has become a movement not a moment , we have seen the ugliest depths of what we are capable of with how we treat those fleeing violence needing protection-and the amazing strength of what we can be and do.....and no matter what , in the opinion of a random aussie girl - plodding along through each day -
the only thing i know for sure is that peace will come again...compassion for those who need it will no longer be an ask , but a given .
let’s not take the easy way ,don’t take the shortcuts this year...take the harder path, the only one that really matters...and that is kindness. be kind. pls be kind, especially when it’s hard. always .
#happynewyear2019 #kindnesschangestheworld
#asylumseekerresourcecentre #knowhowluckyyouare 
#payitforward #thankyoubravewomen #thankyouamazingmen

text:
powerful message to womyn only (and for men that want to stand in solidarity with womyn)

what's your shero's journey?

each of us have experienced various ways of initation on our path back towards wholeness and our power. i want to honor our wounds we have experienced from the patriarch society. be it any form of abuse be is sexually or societal. 
as someone who was abused and sexually abused i found that more then just honoring and healing from it was something even more powerful!

it was when i discovered my power. i dived deep into falling in love with myself. 
rediscovering my self worth, reclaiming my power, returning to my passions, no longer afraid but instead a fierce radiant goddess of love. 
after leaving my ex i have helped many other women leave abusive men. i have always commited to help create a container for other womyn, acting as a sistar, friend and guide (someone that went through those similar experiences, passageways and made it through to the break of dawn to rise again). i want you to all know that you are so so loved. and i honor each of you that have or are currently experiencing abuse. you are not alone. more importantly there are resources and support. including my supporr. over this past year i have helped more womyn then i ever have with womyn coming to heal from trauma around abuse and sexual abuse. even a few men. but let's face it, it's mostly womyn. that's why i know that all that has come to the forefront in venus in scorpio retrograde has been completely to my attention that 2019 i will be dedicating more fully to my work with womyns empowerment.

from collecting money for drives, collections of womyns clothes for dress for success, hygiene products, raising funds towards organizations that end abuse and protect womyn and children, stopping human trafficking. as well as train in volunteer work to help those in domestic violence and those healing from trauma. 
i know my shero's journey was not just my own journey and i helped those that crossed my path to help my sistars heal and rise again. 
but this year has been clear to me that my dedication needs to dive deeper. 💓part 2 below💓 👇
name: Shamanic Healing Tribe🌎🌱🌎

rediscovering my self worth, reclaiming my power, returning to my passions, no longer afraid but instead a fierce radiant goddess of love.

from collecting money for drives, collections of womyns clothes for dress for success, hygiene products, raising funds towards organizations that end abuse and protect womyn and children, stopping human trafficking. as well as train in volunteer work to help those in domestic violence and those healing from trauma. 
i know my shero's journey was not just my own journey and i helped those that crossed my path to help my sistars heal and rise again.

text:
2019 is almost upon us. 2018 has been nothing less than a roller coaster ride. lots of ups and downs, lots of hits and misses, some new beginnings and some endings. more than anything i found confidence of taking up the #100dayartchallenge which i never thought that i could complete. i also made peace with myself about keeping my ig feed real by posting good and not so good art. i also converted my ig handle from personal to business which has given my posts more audience. i just hope that things to get better in 2019 for me and everyone . i hope to see less news of earthquakes, volcanoes, storms,etc. 2018 saw #metoo  movement around the world , and our art world was not left out. hope this next year brings in a safer world which will give equal opportunities to all. . .
.

happy new year everybody!

text:
"the human heart, at whatever age, opens only to the heart that opens in return." - maria edgeworth. 
as we head into #2019 be sure to take this #newyearseve2018 as an opportunity to let go of emotional baggage within.  clear toxic thoughts that have been holding you in a mental prison.  recharge your cells with the highest and purest vibrational energies to set the tone for 2019. 
you can do this by a simple clearing meditation with #soundbath or via youtube, #6phasemeditation #guidingenergymeditation and/or a combo of all while envisioning a clearing and setting your intentions for 2019.  secondly, you can go out in nature and literally ground yourself by planting your bare feet into the ground and recharge with a meditation under the sun.  reawake to your highest potential as a conscious creator; one mind, body and soul. 
#integrativehealing for empowered living!  collaborate with the body and thrive!

release trapped emotions for abundant health, love and happiness.  you can also start by reading the book #theemotioncode by dr. bradley nelson.  the more you hold things in and push them down to hide away, the more you will see your mental physical and emotional health deteriorate.  this is all too real for me as late in 2017 i was effected by a #metoo occurrence.  something i haven't shared with many people.  know there's absolutely no shame in asking for help.  strong and smart people ask for help, always.  this is what we are here for, to help each other.  i vow to myself and have done the work to release all and any emotional trauma that has held me back.  2018 sure was one heck of a ride.  i no longer allow an incident or any single person to encroach my thoughts, manifest in my body as stress, tension, negative energy, or to rob my thoughts.  i connect to my own power and will not settle for anything less and neither should any other soul. 
so, today is the day to welcome a new paradigm of existence. ***the energy you surround yourself with on new years eve defines your entire emerging new year...choose wisely!

#emotioncode #energymedicine #holistichealth #selfhealing  #loveandlight #innerpeace #healing #health #mindset #mentalhealth 👇

text:
•tinder stabbing/dating safety•
😲😲😲
if you missed the 2 ig lives with @donniwiggins the last few weeks this is specifically what we were discussing & warning you about. 🙏🏾my prayers go out to this young lady who was severely injured. all the details are not available yet, however, i will focus on what we do know so far. tap & swipe⬅️...
•
🚨 reminders for 1st dates::
1.  do not go to a secluded or private location, especially a guys home.
2.  meet in a public familiar place, where other people are. there is safety in numbers. 
3. have a safety plan.  know what you will do and how you will escape if things hit the fan. 
4. do not allow your date (a stranger) to pick you up at your home or job. that is specific personal information that he does not need to know yet. 🚨take note➡️
1.police had to tase this man four times ⚡️ 2. he said he was god and the victim was the devil
3.  he died at or on the way to the hospital. 🤔➡️when you put these together that tells me from my experience as a police officer being tased, tasing others, and witnessing people react to being tased that this guy was probably high or under the influence of a drug. pay attention to behavior and listen to your intuition. •in an altered state people do not have the same pain tolerance, strength, and mental capacity as when they are normally uninfluenced. meaning if you are on a date with them and have to fight for your life, it likely may be 10x harder!
🗣please date smarter, remove any opportunities for a man to take advantage of you or harm you. control what you can control, we can’t control another person’s actions. •

text_retweet:
❤️💜💙💚🧡 #endparentshaming #shameproofparenting || #repost @perceptiveparenting
・・・
last week i attended a workshop on childhood trauma presented by echo training (thank you echo training!). i know i'll be digesting for some time what i learned, much of which is personal for me.
. 
there's no way to convey it all in a meme. in short, trauma is ubiquitous, and it can reshape the body and brain. there is treatment for recovery from trauma, which is encouraging.
.
one essential component of recovery is having healthy and attuned relationships, and that's one more reason i'm so grateful for p.e.t. – it teaches communication skills that foster such relationships.
.
i like to imagine a world in which everyone is seen and understood; a world in which everyone has just one person with whom they're attuned. i know personally the power of that kind of relationship, and it's been transformative for me. that's one reason i do what i do.
.
💛
.
#echotraining #echoparenting #childhoodtrauma #developmentaltrauma #traumarecovery #attunement #healthyrelationships #listentounderstand #thebodykeepsthescore #besselvanderkolk #healingoftrauma #braindevelopment #senseofself #bodyandbrain #trust #empathy #traumasurvivor #metoo #neuroplasticity #powerofrelationships #hurtandheal #reclaimyourlife #perceptiveparenting #communicationskills #parenteducation

text:
in 2018, my nye intention was to re-divine masculinity, to open my heart to brothers without and to embrace masculine within. this shift has been a journey of much trust, discernment, discomfort, and growth. this shift has required a sifting out of toxic patriarchal notions from true divine masculinity in all its innately pure glory 🍃 
when i chose to open my heart to conscious masculinity, i opened my eyes to see many bright brothers standing before me, ready to exchange in service, kindness, respect. i also was struck by the sight of men suffering, propelling me into grief & compassion for the ways patriarchy has suppressed & fed the collective male wound. i felt the root of violence as a sad inner child, reaching for his innocence or his mom. after a week of some of the most transformative work i’ve experienced via tantra immersion, i collapsed in tears in the arms of a brother, allowing my womb to grieve for all that had caused my separation from men, while being held in gratitude for this choice of re-union 🙏 
in this way, my heart has expanded to a place my one year ago self could not have imagined ✨ now, i find myself deeply called to work with men in their healing & self-forgiveness and to work with women in this opening for reconciliation. i send light to those who have hurt me most & find solidarity in our divinely innocent sparks. i feel my frustration & devastation for the pain caused by wounds left untended. i allow for more raw grief and rage for the child in me who has been let down by the masculine, full confrontation in service of reconciliation at the root. 
the deepest reverence for men courageously diving into their own healing and heart expansion. the deepest honour for women choosing love. returning to centre, for all relations 🌎
