text:
swipe ➡️ via @artnet @sarahecascone “if you haven’t made it to beth rudin dewoody’s private west palm beach art space the bunker yet, you should know that it is every bit as spectacular as you’ve heard. welcoming visitors during the first-annual new wave art wknd, dewoody and her curator laura dvorkin also arranged to hold a special performance by inner course, a project from rya kleinpeter and tora lópez.the agony of it all, originally staged at brooklyn’s smack mellon over the summer, sees kleinpeter and lópez, outfitted as retro housewives a lá lucille ball, in twin beds. surrounding them is a mountain of outrageously sexist books about women—some well-meaning, others unabashedly misogynistic. they sip wine to console themselves, reading aloud until they break into tears, blowing their noses theatrically and offering visitor tissues.
the piece was hilarious, but also heartbreaking. at first, you think, how ridiculous these books are. then, you remember that someone took the trouble to write each of them—and some quite recently. these words are a reflection of the attitudes of the patriarchy, still deeply ingrained in our society even in the age of #metoo. if you or someone you love doubts the continued relevance for feminism, think again.”

text_retweet:
i turn 56 next year-next month & after 3 broken bones, in my right foot alone & a broken left pinky finger. the ups & downs these few years, losses family, friends,  pets & career was definitely a challenge. learning who i am in those last few months of healing was a ride that few wanna take, care to take or have to take, but this, this road was for me. this path that i am on now, has such light it is amazing & still unbelievable! it is a miracle that i can walk, move, drive, or do yoga. never was i ever open minded enough to believe not only in myself, but in my body-or even my soul.

i have always struggled with my weight, self confidence & i know women shaped like me are not wanted on the media, or sponsors lol and that’s ok! they like to see attractive people in tiny yoga clothes, hahaha you know what is even funnier than that? there is no tiny size when you’re out of shape & over the hill lol! women like us need yoga clothes that are flexible & reliable so our boobs don’t fall out, lol & yet we just deal, we accept, the worlds isolation, because we are not worthy? never! i am very proud of the fullness of my body & the fact that it heals & i get to redo and start over with the grace of god. 
i am here to tell you,  i am so grateful for all the emotional, physical & mental pain i have endured in my life from molestation to bulimia, abuse, heart breaks, judgements to losses. i have become a survivor & climbed out of the darkness of victimization, i have broken free! will i struggle still? hell yes, i will & i will continue to survive no matter what the darkness brings, because i am the light the light i am! happy 56 birthday to me, next month & bring it on life! i am here to inspire, to lift you up & to tell you-you are loved, you matter & you will get through this too! just keep stepping & #believe

text:
man lures girl, 16, via facebook, rapes and abducts her
.
.
a 16-year-old secondary school girl has been rescued after being lured by one vincent idumonyi, abducted and raped in benin, edo state.
.
.
according to reports, idumonyi invited the victim to a hotel, a month after they met on facebook. however, on getting there, the girl was abducted for 3 days.
.
.
the suspect then contacted her family to demand a ransom of n500k before her release, but the family only parted ways with n382,000, before the police traced idumonyi and arrested him.
.
.
in his confessional statement, the suspect admitted that he raped the girl twice after threatening her with a knife and to inject her with a deadly substance. -
____

text:
to say that 2018 was a wild ride would be an understatement of negligent proportions. this year, pain was far too often at the forefront of the national psyche. however, amidst the storm of political, social, and cultural dissonance, there were those who used the chaos as fuel to fight harder for the greater good. cities and counties across the us (and several countries entirely) banned needless single-use plastics in the form of straws and bags, both slow fashion and medicine (oh, and the environment!) benefitted when hemp was reintroduced into the us agricultural scene on a federal level, representation in politics and pop culture alike widened its scope to include significantly more bipoc and people of the lgbt+ community (giving all children a stronger ability to see brighter futures for themselves and their communities, among myriad other benefits to society right now), movements like #timesup and #metoo received international attention and prompted public (and household) conversations that have been painfully silenced for far too long, and mariah carey released a new album. yeah, you read that right. mimi's still at it; things can’t be that bad.▫️⠀
▫️▫️▫️⠀
on a much smaller and more personal scale, this was the year ware went from being a young woman's pipe dream to an entrepreneur's opening act. ware made its way into the physical world in 2018, and for that, i will always remember it fondly. however, it did not materialize from nothing and i in no way did this alone. for those who supported me with their funds and reassurances, for those who spent countless hours covered in paint and sawdust with me, for those who lent me their hard-earned wisdom in the form of advice, for those who took to social media and real-life communication to spread the word, for those who shopped here, for those who keep coming back to do so(!), for those who have let me talk about little else, for those who didn’t take it personally when i didn’t show up to important life events or return phone calls, for those who have been patient and understanding with the growing pains, for those who shared their experience and concerns, my gratitude runs deep. ⠀
(cont'd in comments ⬇️)
name: Ware
tweet_full:
to say that 2018 was a wild ride would be an understatement of negligent proportions. this year, pain was far too often at the forefront of the national psyche. however, amidst the storm of political, social, and cultural dissoce, there were those who used the chaos as fuel to fight harder for the greater good. cities and counties across the us (and several countries entirely) banned needless single-use plastics in the form of straws and bags, both slow fashion and medicine (oh, and the environment!) benefitted when hemp was reintroduced into the us agricultural scene on a federal level, representation in politics and pop culture alike widened its scope to include significan notly more bipoc and people of the lgbt+ community (giving all children a stronger ability to see brighter futures for themselves and their communities, among myriad other benefits to society right now), movements like #timesup and #metoo received international attention and prompted public (and household) conversations that have been painfully silenced for far too long, and mariah carey released a new album. yeah, you read that right. mimi's still at it; things can’t be that bad.▫️⠀
▫️▫️▫️⠀
on a much smaller and more personal scale, this was the year ware went from being a young woman's pipe dream to an entrepreneur's opening act. ware made its way into the physical world in 2018, and for that, i will always remember it fondly. however, it did not materialize from nothing and i in no way did this alone. for those who supported me with their funds and reassurances, for those who spent countless hours covered in paint and sawdust with me, for those who lent me their hard-earned wisdom in the form of advice, for those who took to social media and real-life communication to spread the word, for those who shopped here, for those who keep coming back to do so(!), for those who have let me talk about little else, for those who didn’t take it personally when i didn’t show up to important life events or return phone calls, for those who have been patient and understanding with the growing pains, for those who shared their experience and concerns, my gratitude runs deep. ⠀
(cont'd in comments ⬇️)

text:
happy new year! mimi and i hope you spent the holidays surrounded by good family, good food, and good health. 
we also hope you haven't forgotten about our important project, "i am her". we certainly haven't. especially since in the last year we... * wrote one powerful play; * leveraged six theater experts for advice, editing, etc. * hosted 35 women at a well-received reading; * spoke with three experienced directors; * hired one amazing female director (finalizing contract with plans to announce in january); and
* raised $6,350 towards production!

but the next year also has a lot in store. to read about our #2019goals, check out our latest newsletter at https://bit.ly/2ey1le7. 
#happynewyear #newyear #2018 #2019 #2019resolutions #metoo #believesurvivors #tellyourstory #play #theaterproduction

from  the grammy’s with @redone & @zachwilliamsmusic to the @maryland_music_awards with my boys, sharing the stage with @otownofficial  and @aaroncarter to the @wowfestivalbaltimore stage with @taranajaneen , sharing stories with @midday_maryland abc @951shinefm , @wusa9 (@greatdaywash ), @wtmdradio and @linkedin (@linkedinlocal ), to @lightcitybmore and the legendary @alleyman65 stage, the marathon hasn’t been a clear path but i am grateful for the opportunities, ability to live my dream, friendships made and excited to see what god has in store for 2019! .
.

text: happy new year 2019 everyone! hyvää uutta vuotta 2019! с новым годом 2019 ! 🥂✨🌟🍾🎇 this year 2018 i have been able to step into many people´s shoes; eileen in woderful town the musical, sally bowles in cabaret, myself in solo performance about #metoo and gender equality, one of sondheim´s frogs in the frogs, susan in tick, tick boom, the fate in hadestown, mindi/secretary/dance captain in 9to5 musical, marya antonovna in the goverment inspector and police palmu (nuorempi konstaapeli palmu) in the christmas show. the casting age was 18-24 although i finally had my sweet 16 birthday this year 🎈😉 it was absolute hell at times and i would have not survived without the people around me. 💪🏽❤️ nothing came easy and the hard work shall continue. good luck never hurt anyone and that in mind new year adventures 2019 - bring it on ! 🌟✈️❤️🎬

text:
2018 was a big year for the #metoo movement. looking forward to seeing even more progress in 2019 and helping more survivors find their voice!
✨
🎉
january 2018 ✅ more than 300 women of hollywood form an anti-harassment coalition called times up @timesupnow 🙌🏻
👠
january 2018 ✅ oprah winfrey @oprah says ‘time’s up’ in powerful golden globes speech
🗣
👊🏾
february 2018 ✅ aly raisman @alyraisman along with 203 other victims faced their abuser,larry nassar, giving impact statements 🤸🏻‍♀️
👯‍♀️
on may 25, 2018 ✅ weinstein was charged by new york prosecutors with rape, criminal sex act, sex abuse and sexual misconduct
🗽
🚓
april 2018 ✅ bill cosby was convicted of drugging and molesting a woman 14 years ago in the first big celebrity trial of the #metoo era.
🎬
💪🏻
april 2018 ✅ the new york times and the new yorker won the pulitzer prize for public service monday for breaking the harvey weinstein scandal with reporting that galvanized the #metoo movement and set off a worldwide reckoning over sexual misconduct in the workplace 🏅
📰
september 2018 ✅ christine blasey ford changed the way america views assault victims when she bravely testified before congress about being sexually assaulted by supreme court nominee judge brett kavanaugh when they were in high school. 🏛
👨🏼‍⚖️
november 2018 ✅ the house ethics committee calls for a swift resolution to negotiations over how to change the system for reporting sexual harassment and other abusive workplace behavior on capitol hill.
💼
🏢
#metoo #timesup #goldenglobes2018 #billcosbyguilty #weinsteinarrest #victimimpactstatements #civicduty #christineblaseyfordwebelieveyou #believesurvivors #regainyourvoice #nassarsentencing #amovementnotamoment #progress #morein2019

text:
danke an @eva.liest für die nominierung und @femundo.de für die idee #meine5liebstenromaneaus2018

gar nicht so einfach, weil ich das gar nicht so genau zähle (#solltedaseinvorsatzsein?) und mit hörbüchern, bücherei und eigenen käufen doch ein wenig zusammen kommt. 
so habe ich mich ein wenig umgeschaut und bin zu den folgenden romanen gekommen. vor allem verbinde ich mit allen entweder erinnerungen oder sie haben mich sehr zum nachdenken angeregt. einen blogeintrag gibt es auch dazu (link in bio) ⭐ christian berkel - apfelbaum
eine  wunderbare familiengeschichte im rahmen der deutschen geschichte. ⭐margaret atwood - der report der magd
 ein erschreckend, spannendes buch, was auch im rahmen der #metoo debatte aktueller den je erscheint  und dass obwohl es bereits 1985 erschienen ist. ⭐ian mcewan - kindeswohl
auch wenn er kein unbekannter ist, für mich eine entdeckung des jahres. ein kritisches buch über viele ethische fragen. ⭐lucy fricke - töchter
 ein nachdenkliches buch über töchter, das sterben ,die bilanz aus einem leben mit einem wundervollen ,sarkastischen, trockenem humor. ⭐leïla slimani - dann schlaf auch du
ein richtiger thriller , der einen nachdenklich zurück lässt. 
dazu kamen zum ersten mal einige lesungen in diesem jahr, neuentdeckungen, eine buchmesse und vieles mehr. 😊

auch wenn der spruch auf dem 2. bild mittlerweile inflationär verwendet wird und wahrscheinlich weder von astrid lindgren noch pippi langstrumpf stammt, spiegelt er doch genau wieder, wie mich gerade fühle. ich habe 2018 geliebt doch nun ist es zeit für was neues. klar macht eine andere zahl nicht alles neu, aber zumindest heute fühlt es sich so an. 
ich wünsche allen einen guten rutsch ins neue jahr, viel zum essen und trinken und viele tolle leseeindrücke in 2019. 🎉🍪🥂📚 #bookstagram

text:
2018 i 10 bilder:
* spelade in ett jävligt starkt tv-program om kvinnokampen i #polen åt svt, som troligtvis aldrig kommer sändas pga verkligheten är som en stieg larsson-roman (och jag får väl bli ännu mer lisbeth s...)
* fick se einar på ultraljud för första gången ❤️
* spelade in @varvet med @triumf och preggo-spydde i en papperskorg i vällingby centrum 🙌
* sjöng med ett gäng framförallt magiska kvinnor i globen (#sverigetolkarbowie ) ⚡️
* utbildade företag i ” #metoo- i praktiken” #minupprättelse 💪
* var med och arrangerade #knytblusmanifestation, men @ninarungs & @kickanwicksell var dom verkliga hjältarna (jag gravidspydde mest) 🎀
* åkte till new york och hade klimatångest men var egoist som längtade bort 🙄
* hade hängbuk i 33-gradig värme i västergötland 🤰
* startade ny podd (#faktisktpodd ) och lät kvinnor med koll folkbilda om bla #endometrios och #utbrändhet (podden återkommer nästa år!) 🧠
* födde barn och det var inte ens särskilt jobbigt, pga graviditeten från helvetet äntligen var över 🤱

text:
year 2018, day 365: it began with a fall on day 1 (scroll back to post on jan 1, 2018 :p) but here i am on day 365, standing tall (5.4” is tall no, lol?), and graceful

2018, we made a lot happen

we made me an entrepreneur 
we gave birth to mahi
then too many babies appeared in life
baby in highlight, my daniyaal
we came fashion! *does a little dance* 
we became confidence! *does a rajnikanth pose*
we made it through all the criticism *hi5s*
many lullabies for cats and dogs happened
we found souls that gave wings to those precious dreams
manifested the musical path after lifetimes of waiting
met souls that understood the most absurd spiritual things (like above) and responded and said #metoo
met an army of women of strength who also said #metoo in a very different context
almost moved to the caribbean islands! woohoo
travelled and travelled inside and outside
we loved like no one’s business
we broke like no one’s business
and got back up and became love again
we made it to the tabloids for the right reasons. one for displaying innermost strength and the other for exploding with innermost depths of creativity. #blessed. saying no to all those fancy jobs and positions like ceo finally makes a lot of sense now. 
2018, you taught me that no fear is big enough and you let me experience this first hand

one life, making it the book or movie i couldn’t stop binge reading or watching! and omg, cannot wait for the world to witness all the series and seasons! 😍

thank you 2018, its good to know now why i am here and what my purpose is.  there is such a thing really! 2019, we are set! the world is now ready to see what we are here to do! ❤️ and to everyone who believed in me and stuck by me, thank you. for everyone who didn’t, a bigger thank you. for those who are still on the fence and trying to figure it out, don’t hurt your poor bum so much! haha!

wishing you all the most wonderful new year everyday!

make it happen
-swapna nair.

text: i’ve caught a lot of hell for putting my life out in the open. it seems to many the “highlight reel” is way more appealing. but then there are the private messages and quiet conversations that say, thank you for being real, i needed that. pain can be redeemed if we let it out. 2018 tried to effing kill me. finalizing a painful divorce, selling and buying houses and moving all on my own. multiple break ins at my business. opening my heart only to have it shattered yet again. having a trusted  christian mentor verbally assault me. (#metoo) my kid blowing her knee out and watching yet another of her dreams be crushed on top of a divorce. and learning to navigate life without a crutch. and so much more.., i have faced so many fears this year. not by choice. looking back, i think, how in the hell did i survive all that??? man, i don’t know, but i did. i survived, and i’m on my face in gratitude for it. yes, gratitude, because i know right now that i can face whatever bullshit life throws at me. i am a badass. 2019 is already full of opportunities that scare the shit out of me but i am so ready. i can’t even wait to share it all. fear is a lie and it’s time to rise! #fearisalie #gratitude #2019imcomingforyou
name: Danea Christine

text:
when i look back, i want to see how everything in my life propelled me forward. i want to be able to say how the hurt and pain were exactly what i needed to help me step into my best self.
~
what an incredible year of surrender in my life. there’s been such exhilaration, some challenges, some sadness, but more importantly tremendous growth. there’s been some periods of intense trials, but even through the tears and stressful moments, there is a peace that transcends, that’s unexplainable, and beyond what my tiny little mind can comprehend. ~
so as we step into the new year, i hope you’ll learn to embrace all these moments, whether it appears to be good or bad, and trust that it is only leading you to your best self. ~
thank you for holding my hand through my life’s journey, as i hope i have held yours. sending you all much love, prosperity, and good vibes always.
thank you 2018. next!! 🎊🍾🥂🎉
~

text:
hiding can be a contemplative retreat. it can be a place of solace. hiding is sometimes the preparation zone before one can come out anew or refreshed. (@davidjwhyte speaks to this in his poetry). it can also be very lonely residing in isolation. so often trauma survivors get stuck hiding and we desperately yearn to be found. to be seen. to be heard. it is quite a disaster to not experience deep, safe connection. i will say, i have found that it is possible. trauma survivors can connect. we can be seen. and loved in a safe way. it is an essential part of the healing process. scary? of course! but anything worthwhile evokes fear at first. hide if you need to, just don’t hide too long. and try when you can to find someone safe to connect with. you are soooo worth it. ❤️

text:
can 'no' mean 'yes'?
have you ever interpreted a no to yes? if yes so please  stop reading it. you may not like it. 
under any circumstances 'no' 'i don't want to' 'i am not comfortable' 'not right now' can be interpreted as 'yes' 'sure' or 'alright'. john oliver said "consent is like boxing if both people do not agree to it, then one person is committing a crime" 
no doesn't mean yes, later or convince me. wearing tight clothes is not an invitation, we are not playing "hard to get".
consent in dictionary means "permission of something to happen or agreement to do something". it's the last day of 2018, and 2019 is going to begin soon. take no shame in talking about anything that happened to you or your loved ones, stop protecting the culprit or blaming the victim, stop slut shaming or objectifying bodies. nowadays, people have recently started to become more and more aware about this topic as more women are coming out and letting everyone know about their stories to raise awareness about this issue.
i know this is quite a heavy subject but shying away from open communication does more harm than good. as always your input is very much appreciated. so let’s talk about it all.

text:
youtube videon 
gott nytt år önskar metood!

några av oss i den malmöitiska delen ur #konstnärligfrihet har skapat en egen video för att stötta våra medsyskon i #tystnadtagning-uppropet.

efter #metoo’s genombrott under 2018 sprängs vi av lust att skapa, det spänner, det stramar och det knakar, det är förändringsarbete på konstområdet. det finns myriader av underbara kulturarbetare!

filmen är en kollektiv och anonym insats och avsändaren är den löst sammansatta gruppen metood - en arbetsgrupp för förändringsarbete inom konstområdet i malmö. i sökandet efter nya metoder att hantera det som #metoo synliggjorde föddes rörelsen metooder och vi jobbar med ett levande, sökande arbete för en mer jämlik kulturvärld. 
lägg till vår film i din nyårsplaylist tillsammans med #tystnadtagning’s! 
sprid i dina sociala medier, låt den få vingar och flyg in i 2019 med oss! #greatmindsthinkalike
tillsammans är vi starka, tillsammans kan vi förändra och vi är redan tillsammans!

ett gott nytt år och må förändringsarbetet sprida sig över hela världen i “ring klocka, ring”. ytterligare infotext:

metood verkar för att förhindra sexuella trakasserier och övertramp, exponera informella maktstrukturer och krossa tystnadskulturen inom konstvärlden.
gruppen föddes ur #metoo-rörelsen och är separatistisk med ett intersektionellt perspektiv för alla personer som identifierar sig som kvinnor, trans eller icke-binära.
varmt välkomna att ansluta er till oss - alla perspektiv och erfarenheter behövs för att vi ska kunna få ett grundläggande förändringsarbete i stånd. tillsammans värker vi fram våra mål och arbetar mot långsiktiga stordåd!

https://www.facebook.com/metooder/
metooder@gmail.com

text:
the true babies of the family and me 😝
.
this was a wip for inktober 2018 but unfortunately, a lot of things happened that month...it was a hard time for me... so, i wasn't able to finish this piece. despite all the downfalls, i am grateful for the never-ending support of my dear family and close friends. 😌
.
one of the things that i am thankful for 2018 is having these babies added to our family. taking care of them might have been stressful, especially to my mother, but they surely brought joy in our family.(i thought it was a cute idea to make an illustration of them 😝)
.
thank you 2018, for all the memories, relationships, preparations, & lessons.
now, i am still healing... and eager to make more finished artworks (because my 2018 works are mostly wips 😝). and hoping that everything will be much better in 2019.
.
a blessed, happy, & prosperous 2019 to all of us. happy new year!

text:
#янебаюсясказаць #metoo
*мам, калі раптам ты даведаешся пра гэта раней, чым я буду здольная распавесці, калі нехта з тваіх сябровак, з тых, хто чытае мой інстаграм, завядзе пра гэта гаворку, калі незнарок ты сама захочаш праглядзець мае пасты ў пошуку прыгожых фотаздымкаў з апошняга шпацыру з сяброўкай-фатографам, даруй. даруй, калі ласка.
я табе давяраю. цалкам.
я б даверыла і наступнае, бо зараз на гэтую тэму літаральна крычу ў інстаграме некалькім сотням чалавек, але я люблю цябе. занадта моцна для таго, каб распавядаць такія гісторыі гледзячы ў вочы. пасля таго, што адбылося, я доўга не магла зазірнуць нават у свае - баялася* - дзякуй, што ўсё ж такі паразмаўлялі. дзякуй, што зразумела. 
дзякуючы вам з татам, я пераканалася: казаць пра такое не сорамна.

20-га чэрвеня 2018 года. я, без асаблівага жадання, але больш-менш сумленна рыхтавалася да цт па англійскай мове. заскочыўшы зраніцы ў дзіцячую паліклініку, каб атрымаць даведку, я накіравалася ў «зярно», дзе на працягу некаторага часу рабіла тэсты. каля другой гадзіны дня я выйшла адтуль, села ў альтанку ў двары і запаліла. да мяне падышоў мужчына.

я б дала яму гадоў сорак-пяцьдзясят. ён быў апрануты ў трэнікі і расцягнутую майку, на нагах былі нейкія кросы, некалі паголеныя валасы ўжо пачалі адрастаць. дзядзька завёў са мной гаворку пра жыццё-быццё, а я на той момант шмат кантактавала з хлопцамі, якія такога падыходу ні разу не баяліся і актыўна, з доляй жарту, падтрымлівалі дыялог з алкаголікамі ля ўніверсама «цэнтральны». я ўжо паспела забыцца, што факт нараджэння дзяўчынай вельмі моцна ўплывае на далейшае развіццё падзей.

мужчына падышоў да мяне і пачаў скардзіцца на тое, што ўсё спрабуе кінуць паліць, але ніяк не атрымліваецца і яму ну вельмі хочацца. вырашаўшы, што ўсё, што яму трэба ад мяне, абмяжоўваецца адной цыгарэтай, я працягнула яму пачак. ён дастаў адтуль адну. і сеў побач. ⬇️

дзякуючы вам з татам, я пераканалася: казаць пра такое не сорамна.

20-га чэрвеня 2018 года. я, без асаблівага жадання, але больш-менш сумленна рыхтавалася да цт па англійскай мове. заскочыўшы зраніцы ў дзіцячую паліклініку, каб атрымаць даведку, я накіравалася ў «зярно», дзе на працягу некаторага часу рабіла тэсты. каля другой гадзіны дня я выйшла адтуль, села ў альтанку ў двары і запаліла. да мяне падышоў мужчына.

я б дала яму гадоў сорак-пяцьдзясят. ён быў апрануты ў трэнікі і расцягнутую майку, на нагах былі нейкія кросы, некалі паголеныя валасы ўжо пачалі адрастаць. дзядзька завёў са мной гаворку пра жыццё-быццё, а я на той момант шмат кантактавала з хлопцамі, якія такога падыходу ні разу не баяліся і актыўна, з доляй жарту, падтрымлівалі дыялог з алкаголікамі ля ўніверсама «цэнтральны». я ўжо паспела забыцца, што факт нараджэння дзяўчынай вельмі моцна ўплывае на далейшае развіццё падзей.

мужчына падышоў да мяне і пачаў скардзіцца на тое, што ўсё спрабуе кінуць паліць, але ніяк не атрымліваецца і яму ну вельмі хочацца. вырашаўшы, што ўсё, што яму трэба ад мяне, абмяжоўваецца адной цыгарэтай, я працягнула яму пачак. ён дастаў адтуль адну. і сеў побач. ⬇️

text:
बच्चियों को आपके साथ की ज़रुरत है। छोटे छोटे गाँव और कस्बों में रहने वाली नन्ही नन्ही गुड़ियाएं यह आस लगा कर बैठी रहती हैं की शायद किसी दिन भगवान उनकी मदद करेगा। दुनिया भर की पीड़ा सहकर भी जो अपने चेहरे पर ज़रा सी डगमगाहट नहीं आने देती, वह बच्चियां भी आपसे उम्मीदें रखती हैं। ngo जीवन अर्थ फाउंडेशन आपसे निवेदन करता है कि इस नव वर्ष आप लोग इन बच्चियों कि खुशियों के लिए उनके लिए एक साल के सेनेटरी पैड्स का बंदोबस्त कर सकेंगे। कृपया ngo को दान करने के लिए ngo की वेबसाइट या ngo को paytm (8104107086) पर दान करके ngo एवं इन बच्चियों का मनोबल बढ़ाएं।
________

translation:

the girls need your support. small and little girls in the villages look after god in a hope that he’ll help them. the ones who face a lot of troubles in their daily day to day lives, but they still don't let that pain reflect in their smile or on their face. even those girls have expectations from you.

ngo jeevan arth foundation requests you to sponsor yearly sanitary pads for a girl, this new year. buy them a new year gift they really need.

you can donate to the ngo from our website: www.jeevanarth.org or you can donate via paytm @ 8104107086

text:
personally and politically, 2018 was a massive year. 
for myself it was a year that saw us relocate, again, and find our feet, all over again. a year full of travel and adventure, missing old friends, making new ones, new languages, new challenges. a year of change.  but on the wider, worldwide scale it was unbelievable. the #metoo movement that picked up pace and is now showing actual tangible results that have trickled down to our everyday lives is encouraging. for too long we have all lived in a normal where we brush off behaviour that is ‘just a joke’. listening to the news and podcasts regularly this year has really woken me up to the realities of other people’s lives and the struggles large groups around the world face on a daily basis. it’s made me think a lot about words i’ve used and attitudes i’ve had in the past. and how i’m too old to blame my upbringing on stereotypes that i’ve held about certain types of people as an excuse to be dismissive of their problems. when i think about how much i want everyone to come together to fight the patriarchal systems, it makes me realise how i need to fight to change other systems and stereotypes that don’t necessarily affect me but are just as important to all of us living harmoniously together. 
2018 has been full of positives and i’m excited about 2019!
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
dear 2018,
woof. big woof. a lot of big fuck you's and a lot of thank you's.
to start the year off, you gave me my first bartending job (something i had wanted for a while). that same week, you broke my heart and showed me the darkness in someone who i was manipulated into loving. that same week (and months that followed), i was introduced to some ladies who i'll forever have a special bond with. 2018, you taught me that exposing a sexual predator (if you want to do it right) will take 6 months. you taught me what the fuck it is to be someone with a voice...you taught me how important the #metoo and #timesup movement is for me and should be for everyone and for that, i am grateful. you showed me who the real ones are. you showed me who the fake ones are. you taught me that when you are going through hell, the fake friends will drop you like an empty tito's bottle in the trash on a busy weekend night service and the real ones will keep you like a bottle of pappy. you taught me that women can victim blame too. you taught me more than before about agave distillates (i'm not a scientist but i'm pretty sure my brain and liver are pretty much like...60% mezcal). you gave me a job at a pretty cool bar and taught me how to boss at high volume. you brought me closer to the ones who not only have empathy for what's going on in the world, but who actually want to start a conversation to change it. you made me realize how important denver is to me and how i should visit more. you gave me pink/purple hair and microbladed eyebrows. you brought me to washington. i'll never forget the meal i had and how it made my dad and i teary eyed. you retaught me that i do not put up with bullshit, which caused me to leave my 3 year long yoga teaching gig. you taught me more and more about sex and sex positivity and how much i love talking about these things.
you taught me how to have more than 4 orgasms in a row (highlight). you taught me that it takes over a year to launch a podcast. 2018, you wild. as much as i wana say i hate you, i wana say thank you. for everything. the negatives and the positives and so much more. cheers to you and goodbye. ✌🏼🥂

text:
what a year it has been! 2018 has been a lot for many reasons, but a particularly special year of becoming. this year i found myself-
taking risks l believed in and owning them,
making time to cut through everyday chaos and be more present and accepting the certainty of ambiguity and transience in life

the year in highlights-
2018 in particular, constantly demanded dialogue around what it means to be a woman. it was a year that unfolded to the world- larry nassar, a deeply unsettling kavanaugh hearing, to throwing open the  #metoo floodgates within the creative industry in india. meanwhile, it was a year where i met some of the most inspirational and phenomenal women who are now my mentors, colleagues and friends, each teaching me what it means to own, defy or navigate gender in their personal and professional lives. i found myself consistently in female owned, led teams and walked into more client meetings with balanced gender ratios.

i read recently that we travel not to move, but to be moved. and the highlight of my work this year between hours in transit has to be the strangers who let me into their homes and lives. where my refrain of asking ‘why’ as a researcher led to deeper, fundamental learnings that cut through our disparate circumstances. it made me emotional but gave me opportunities and timely reminders to pause, reflect, and be grateful for my privilege, good health, safety, and socioeconomic status.

my strongest and earliest influences resurfaced this year, but this time around i saw my art evolve into rigorous contemplative practice. a safe space that records so surely, while challenging the impermanence of thoughts and feelings. 
and finally, i find myself in deep gratitude for the people in my life who embraced me with love and care, redefining what home or family could or should be. thank you for letting me be a part of your year. your stories and silent struggles are not unseen, they inspire me.

my name anjali - means prayer or offering and for today and this year, i am extremely grateful. and as i move into 2019, i take with me, words from neil gaiman- “be bold. be rebellious. choose art. it matters.”
